lternatives to promote sustainable crop production.\", \"storage_advice\": {\"duration\": \"up to 12 months\", \"humidity\": \"less than 40%\", \"warnings\": [\"Avoid storage in direct sunlight or high-temperature areas.\"], \"temperature\": \"below 20°C\", \"recommendation\": \"Store wheat in a cool, dry place with proper ventilation to maintain quality.\"}, \"risk_assessment\": {\"spread_risk\": \"Low, as drought stress is not contagious, but neighboring crops may be affected by similar weather conditions.\", \"economic_impact\": \"Significant, due to potential yield loss and reduced crop quality.\", \"current_risk_level\": \"Critical\", \"yield_loss_estimate\": \"20-30% due to drought stress and stunted growth.\"}, \"fertilizer_advice\": {\"dosage\": \"225 kg/ha\", \"method\": \"Broadcast application\", \"timing\": \"Apply basal fertilizer at sowing, and top-dressing 21 and 42 days after sowing.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:45\", \"current_need\": \"The crop is experiencing drought stress and requires balanced fertilization to support recovery.\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"NPK Fertilizer\"}, \"immediate_actions\": [\"Action within 24 hours: Irrigate the wheat crop to reduce drought stress and prevent further damage.\", \"Action within 48 hours: Apply a foliar spray of micronutrients, such as zinc and iron, to support plant health and stress recovery.\"], \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Irrigate the crop to alleviate drought stress.\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply foliar spray of micronutrients to support plant health.\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Monitor crop condition and adjust fertilization and irrigation strategies as needed.\"], \"long_term\": [\"Implement conservation agriculture practices, such as mulching and cover cropping, to improve soil health and reduce drought risk.\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Precaution 1: Monitor weather forecasts to anticipate and prepare for potential heatwaves or dry spells.\", \"Precaution 2: Implement windbreaks or other protective measures to reduce wind damage and moisture loss.\"], \"organic_alternatives\": [\"Use organic fertilizers, such as compost or manure, to promote soil health and plant growth.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Implement irrigation to alleviate drought stress, focusing on efficient water use to minimize waste.\", \"Step 2: Apply a balanced fertilizer with a ratio of 120:60:45 NPK to promote healthy plant growth and stress tolerance.\"], \"harvest_recommendations\": {\"method\": \"Combine harvester or sickle/scythe, depending on crop condition and farmer preference.\", \"readiness\": \"The crop is not yet ready for harvest due to drought stress and stunted growth.\", \"post_harvest\": \"Dry the harvested crop to 12% moisture content to ensure proper storage and quality.\", \"estimated_date\": \"Delayed by 1-2 weeks due to drought stress.\"}}','[{\"content\": \"Wheat (Triticum aestivum) cultivation: Sow in cool weather (10–25°C). Growth duration: 100–130 days. NPK: 120:60:40 kg/ha. Harvest when grain moisture is 14% or less. Store at <15°C in dry conditions.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.0449}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3408}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3652}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4831}]',28.6139,77.209,58.39,'completed','','2026-06-10 07:11:55.027342','2026-06-10 07:12:53.428191'),(13,'crop_images/cb5bb8f8aabf4117871d8130a38853a5.png','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',28.6139,77.209,97.39,'failed','Could not parse Gemini response as JSON: No JSON object found: line 1 column 1 (char 0)','2026-06-10 07:20:24.259119','2026-06-10 07:22:01.667983'),(14,'crop_images/bfe39d62519045098622b4bed3572f85.png','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',28.6139,77.209,NULL,'processing','','2026-06-10 07:26:12.750310','2026-06-10 07:26:12.750310'),(15,'crop_images/d159895c7161422d99307c53e49d1c60.png','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',28.6139,77.209,599.72,'failed','Gemini Vision API failed: 504 Deadline expired before operation could complete.','2026-06-10 07:35:28.125564','2026-06-10 07:45:27.858423'),(16,'crop_images/7db92e30d7544ddbb369199b920d0171.png','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',28.6139,77.209,24.15,'failed','Could not parse Gemini response as JSON: No JSON object found: line 1 column 1 (char 0)','2026-06-10 08:05:49.808950','2026-06-10 08:06:13.998078'),(17,'crop_images/bb46b9e0688a41dfba661e5bceb8053e.png','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',28.6139,77.209,7.14,'failed','Gemini Vision API failed: Gemini Vision API failed after 3 retries: 429 You exceeded your current quota, please check your plan and billing details. For more information on this error, head to: https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/rate-limits. To monitor your current usage, head to: https://ai.dev/rate-limit. \n* Quota exceeded for metric: generativelanguage.googleapis.com/generate_co