ion, especially at the edges of affected areas\"]','Diseased',17,'Critical','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained, pH 6.0-6.8\", \"family\": \"Solanaceae\", \"origin\": \"South America\", \"climate\": \"Temperate to tropical\", \"crop_name\": \"Tomato\", \"description\": \"Tomato is a warm-season crop that requires full sun and well-drained soil to produce high yields. It is a versatile crop that can be grown in a variety of environments, from small gardens to large commercial farms. With proper care, tomato plants can produce an abundance of fruit throughout the growing season.\", \"growth_duration\": \"60-90\", \"scientific_name\": \"Solanum lycopersicum\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate to high\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Infection by Phytophthora infestans\", \"Abundant moisture\"], \"symptoms\": [\"Water-soaked, oily, pale or dark-green or brown/black, circular or irregular lesions near leaflet margins\", \"Leaf and stem necrosis\", \"Fruit rot and eventual plant death\"], \"treatments\": [\"Remove infected plants or plant parts\", \"Apply fungicides\", \"Improve air circulation\"], \"precautions\": [\"Inspect plants regularly for symptoms\", \"Avoid overhead irrigation\", \"Use resistant cultivars\"], \"disease_name\": \"Late Blight\", \"pathogen_name\": \"Phytophthora infestans\", \"pathogen_type\": \"Fungal\", \"chemical_control\": \"Chlorothalonil or copper-based fungicides at recommended dosages\", \"biological_control\": \"Introduction of natural predators or parasites of the pathogen, such as Trichoderma harzianum\", \"favorable_conditions\": \"High humidity and cool temperatures\"}','{\"tips\": [\"monitor for ethylene production\", \"keep away from citrus treated with biphenyl\"], \"do_not\": [\"store with pears\", \"store with ethylene sensitive products\"], \"humidity\": \"90-95\", \"crop_name\": \"Tomato\", \"packaging\": \"ventilated containers\", \"shelf_life\": \"7-14 days\", \"temperature\": \"0-2\", \"storage_type\": \"cold room\", \"pre_storage_treatment\": \