-15\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 37.6, \"temp_min_c\": 26.3, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 10.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.6}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-16\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 40.3, \"temp_min_c\": 26.8, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 10.7, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.2}], \"agricultural_advisory\": [\"⚠️ Extreme heat: irrigate crops early morning or evening.\", \"? Low humidity: increase irrigation frequency.\"]}','{\"summary\": \"The tomato crop is currently under severe threat from Late Blight, with a critical health score of 17.0/100. Immediate actions are necessary to control the disease spread, including removing infected plant parts, applying copper-based fungicides, and implementing integrated pest management strategies. The farmer should also monitor weather conditions closely and take necessary precautions to protect the crop. With prompt and effective management, the crop can still be salvaged, but significant yield loss and economic impact are expected.\", \"storage_advice\": {\"duration\": \"7-14 days\", \"humidity\": \"90-95%\", \"warnings\": [\"Do not store tomatoes with pears or ethylene-sensitive products.\"], \"temperature\": \"0-2°C\", \"recommendation\": \"Store tomatoes in a cool, dry place with adequate ventilation to prevent moisture accumulation.\"}, \"risk_assessment\": {\"spread_risk\": \"High risk of disease spread to neighboring plants and fields\", \"economic_impact\": \"Significant economic impact due to potential yield loss and increased management costs\", \"current_risk_level\": \"Critical\", \"yield_loss_estimate\": \"Potential yield loss of 20-50% due to disease spread\"}, \"fertilizer_advice\": {\"dosage\": \"200-300 kg/ha\", \"method\": \"Broadcast application\", \"timing\": \"Basal application at transplanting, followed by top-dressing 21 and 42 days after sowing.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"5-10-10\", \"current_need\": \"The current fertilizer need is balanced, with a focus on promoting healthy plant growth and disease resistance.\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"Balanced Fertilizer (5-10-10 NPK)\"}, \"immediate_actions\": [\"Action within 24 hours: Remove and destroy all infected plant parts to prevent further spread of the disease.\", \"Action within 48 hours: Apply a fungicide with a different mode of action to prevent the development of resistance.\"], \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Remove and destroy infected plant parts, apply copper-based fungicides\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply a fungicide with a different mode of action, monitor weather conditions and crop health\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue to monitor crop health, apply top-dressing fertilizers as recommended\"], \"long_term\": [\"Implement integrated pest management strategies, consider using resistant varieties in future plantings\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Precaution 1: Monitor weather conditions closely, as high temperatures and low humidity can exacerbate disease spread.\", \"Precaution 2: Be prepared for potential rain events, which can increase the risk of disease spread, and take necessary precautions to protect the crop.\"], \"organic_alternatives\": [\"Copper-based fungicides, neem oil, and bicarbonate-based fungicides\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Apply copper-based fungicides to control the spread of Late Blight, ensuring to follow the recommended dosage and application method.\", \"Step 2: Implement integrated pest management strategies, including crop rotation, sanitation, and the use of resistant varieties, to reduce the risk of disease recurrence.\"], \"harvest_recommendations\": {\"method\": \"Hand-picking or mechanical harvesting, depending on the farm\'s equipment and resources.\", \"readiness\": \"Tomatoes are ready to harvest when they reach full ripeness, indicated by a color change, softening of the skin, and full ripeness.\", \"post_harvest\": \"Grade, clean, and cool the harvested tomatoes to 1°C to maintain quality and extend shelf life.\", \"estimated_date\": \