0.6}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-16\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 38.6, \"temp_min_c\": 26.3, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 10.7, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.2}], \"agricultural_advisory\": [\"⚠️ Extreme heat: irrigate crops early morning or evening.\", \"? Low humidity: increase irrigation frequency.\"]}','{\"summary\": \"The wheat crop is under critical drought stress, with widespread yellowing and senescence of foliage. Immediate irrigation and application of micronutrients are necessary to alleviate stress and promote recovery. A balanced fertilizer application and implementation of conservation agriculture practices can help promote healthy growth and reduce the risk of disease outbreaks. The crop is not yet ready for harvest, and the estimated date will depend on the recovery of the crop and the variety\'s growth duration.\", \"storage_advice\": {\"duration\": \"up to 12 months\", \"humidity\": \"below 40%\", \"warnings\": [\"Avoid storage in areas with high humidity or temperature fluctuations.\"], \"temperature\": \"below 15°C\", \"recommendation\": \"Store the wheat in a cool, dry place to maintain its quality.\"}, \"risk_assessment\": {\"spread_risk\": \"high risk of disease spread due to weakened crop condition\", \"economic_impact\": \"significant economic impact due to potential yield loss and reduced crop quality\", \"current_risk_level\": \"Critical\", \"yield_loss_estimate\": \"potential yield loss of 20-30% due to drought stress\"}, \"fertilizer_advice\": {\"dosage\": \"150 kg/ha N, 26.3 kg/ha P, 33.3 kg/ha K\", \"method\": \"broadcast\", \"timing\": \"at sowing or as a top-dressing after the first irrigation\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:26.3:33.3\", \"current_need\": \"The crop is under drought stress and may benefit from a balanced fertilizer application.\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"NPK Mixture\"}, \"immediate_actions\": [\"Action within 24 hours: Irrigate the field to reduce drought stress, and apply a foliar spray of micronutrients to help with stress recovery.\", \"Action within 48 hours: Assess the field for any signs of pest or disease outbreaks that may be exacerbated by the drought stress.\"], \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Irrigate the field and apply a foliar spray of micronutrients\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Monitor the field for signs of recovery and assess for any pest or disease outbreaks\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Apply a balanced fertilizer to promote healthy growth and stress recovery\"], \"long_term\": [\"Implement conservation agriculture practices to reduce soil erosion and improve soil health\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Precaution 1: Monitor weather forecasts to anticipate and prepare for potential extreme weather events.\", \"Precaution 2: Implement windbreaks or other protective measures to reduce the impact of strong winds on the crop.\"], \"organic_alternatives\": [\"use of organic fertilizers, such as compost or manure, and implementation of conservation agriculture practices\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Implement irrigation to alleviate drought stress, focusing on the most affected areas.\", \"Step 2: Apply a balanced fertilizer with a suitable NPK ratio to promote healthy growth and stress recovery.\"], \"harvest_recommendations\": {\"method\": \"both manual and mechanical harvesting methods can be used\", \"readiness\": \"The crop is not yet ready for harvest due to drought stress.\", \"post_harvest\": \"dry the grain to a moisture content of 14% or less to ensure proper storage\", \"estimated_date\": \"dependent on the recovery of the crop and the variety\'s growth duration\"}}','[{\"content\": \"Wheat (Triticum aestivum) cultivation: Sow in cool weather (10–25°C). Growth duration: 100–130 days. NPK: 120:60:40 kg/ha. Harvest when grain moisture is 14% or less. Store at <15°C in dry conditions.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.0449}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3408}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3652}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4831}]',28.6139,77.209,35.08,'completed','','2026-06-10 08:21:35.463131','2026-06-10 08:22:10.550502'),(25,'crop_images/e446309d60b94b68a6b6455cce23c419.png','Tomato','Late Blight',95,'[\"Large, irregular, dark brown necrotic lesions on leaf blade\", \"Yellow chlorotic halos surrounding necrotic lesions\", \"White, fuzzy, downy fungal growth visible on leaf surface, particularly along edges and some lesion areas\", \"Leaf curling and distortion\"]','Diseased',17,'Critical','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained, fertile soil with pH 6.0-6.8\", \"family\": \"Solanaceae\", \"origin\": \"South America\", \"climate\": \"Warm and temperate\", \"crop_name\": \"Tomato\", \"description\": \"Tomato is a warm-season crop that requires full sun and well-drained soil to produce high yields. It is a versatile crop that can be grown in a variety of environments, from small gardens to large commercial farms. Tomatoes are a good source of essential nutrients like vitamin C and lycopene.\", \"growth_duration\": \"60-90\", \"scientific_name\": \"Solanum lycopersicum\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate to high irrigation\"}','{\"causes\": [\"infection by the pathogen\", \"abundant moisture\"], \"symptoms\": [\"water-soaked, oily, pale or dark-green or brown/black, circular or irregular lesions near leaflet margins\", \"leaf and stem necrosis\", \"fruit rot\"], \"treatment\": [\"removal of infected plants\", \"application of fungicides\"], \"prevention\": [\"inspection of the fruit and foliage\", \"maintenance of good hygiene practices\"], \"precautions\": [\"avoiding excessive moisture\", \"monitoring for secondary infections\"], \"disease_name\": \"Late Blight\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"fruit\"], \"disease_progression\": \"The disease spreads to the rest of the foliage, leading to extensive defoliation, and can also infect tomato seed and fruit, causing soft-rot disease.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"immediately removing infected plants to prevent further spread\", \"applying fungicides to prevent infection of healthy plants\"]}','{\"shelf_life\": \"1-2 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"cold room\", \"humidity_range\": \"90-95%\", \"temperature_range\": \"0-2°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"separate from pears and other ethylene sensitive products, high ventilation, low light and high sanitation\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"cooling, sorting, gentle handling to avoid bruising\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"3-5 days\"}','{\"dosage\": \"follow instructions on the fertilizer package\", \"npk_ratio\": \"5:10:10\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc, Boron, Iron\", \"application_method\": \"broadcast or furrow\", \"application_timing\": \"after soil test, basal at sowing or top dressing after 3-4 true leaves\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"NPK 5-10-10\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"manual\", \"harvest_duration\": \"65-100 days\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"early morning\", \"equipment_required\": [\"pruning shears\", \"gloves\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"fru