ad, ideally in the early morning when the plants are dry\", \"storage_advice\": \"Store harvested tomatoes in a cool, dry place to prevent further disease spread, ideally in a cold room with temperature range 0-2°C and humidity range 90-95%\", \"fertilizer_advice\": \"Adjust fertilizer application to promote healthy plant growth, using NPK 5-10-10 and micronutrients Zinc, Boron, and Iron\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Apply copper-based fungicides to control the spread of Late Blight\", \"Immediate Action 2: Remove and destroy infected leaves and stems to prevent further disease spread\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Avoid overhead irrigation to prevent moisture on leaves, instead use drip irrigation to reduce humidity and prevent disease spread\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Apply copper-based fungicides\", \"Remove infected leaves and stems\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Implement fungicide spray schedule\", \"Ensure good air circulation\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Monitor disease spread\", \"Adjust fertilizer application\"], \"long_term\": [\"Implement integrated pest management strategies\", \"Consider crop rotation to prevent disease buildup\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Avoid spraying fungicides during high winds or rain\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor temperature and humidity levels to prevent disease spread\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Implement a 7-10 day fungicide spray schedule using copper-based products\", \"Step 2: Ensure good air circulation and remove weeds to reduce humidity and prevent disease spread\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Falling\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Wholesale Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"Optimal time to sell tomatoes is during the summer season\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Expected price movement in next 30 days is a decrease of 10-15%\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Further disease spread and crop loss\", \"Risk 2: Reduced market price due to diseased crop\"], \"crop_status\": \"Diseased\", \"health_score\": \"17.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Critical\", \"disease_status\": \"Late Blight\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The tomato crop is severely affected by Late Blight, with a health score of 17.0/100. Immediate action is required to control the disease spread and prevent further crop loss. The farmer should implement a disease management plan, harvest tomatoes as soon as possible, and consider adjusting fertilizer application to promote healthy plant growth. The current weather conditions and market trends should also be taken into account to minimize losses and optimize crop yield.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement disease management plan to control Late Blight\", \"Recommendation 2: Harvest tomatoes as soon as possible to prevent further disease spread\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"22%\", \"wind_speed\": \"13.3 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: High temperature and low humidity may exacerbate disease spread\", \"Risk 2: Light drizzle may increase moisture on leaves and promote disease spread\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"The farmer should harvest early to prevent further disease spread, considering the weather forecast\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Light Drizzle\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is not safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today due to high winds and light drizzle\", \"current_temperature\": \"41.9°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Avoid spraying fungicides during high winds or rain\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor temperature and humidity levels to prevent disease spread\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Late Blight (Phytophthora infestans) is a devastating disease of tomato and potato. Symptoms include dark, water-soaked lesions on leaves and stems that rapidly expand. Management: Apply copper-based fungicides. Remove infected plants. Use resistant varieties. Avoid overhead irrigation.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"source\": \"plantvillage.psu.edu\", \"disease\": \"Late Blight\"}, \"relevance\": 0.5068}, {\"content\": \"Tomato cultivation requires well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0–7.0. Scientific name: Solanum lycopersicum. Growth duration: 60–90 days after transplanting. NPK recommendation: 120:60:60 kg/ha. Requires staking for indeterminate varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.029}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3504}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.369}]',28.6139,77.209,126.67,'completed','','2026-06-10 08:30:06.551456','2026-06-10 08:32:13.226536'),(26,'crop_images/71c00ab6f4d84209a95ecb9918e99565.webp','Cereal Grain (likely Wheat, Barley, or Oats)','Healthy',90,'[\"Uniformly green foliage\", \"Vigorous growth habit\", \"No visible lesions, spots, or necrotic areas\", \"No signs of pest feeding or presence\", \"No widespread chlorosis or stunting\", \"Minor, localized yellowing on tips of some older leaves\"]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Unknown\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Unknown\", \"climate\": \"Cool season\", \"crop_name\": \"Cereal Grain (likely Wheat, Barley, or Oats)\", \"description\": \"Barley is a