chedules according to weather forecasts to prevent water stress\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Wheat (Triticum aestivum) cultivation: Sow in cool weather (10–25°C). Growth duration: 100–130 days. NPK: 120:60:40 kg/ha. Harvest when grain moisture is 14% or less. Store at <15°C in dry conditions.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2188}, {\"content\": \"Rice Blast (Pyricularia oryzae) is the most destructive rice disease globally. Symptoms: diamond-shaped lesions on leaves, neck rot at panicle. Management: Balanced nitrogen, silicon fertilization, fungicide sprays at boot stage.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Rice\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Rice Blast\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2568}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2589}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2882}]',28.6139,77.209,24.19,'completed','','2026-06-10 08:34:12.803354','2026-06-10 08:34:37.001153'),(27,'crop_images/c15f9f431b41452995ca9fc4747d5c7f.png','Wheat','None detected',85,'[\"Widespread yellowing of foliage\", \"Extensive browning and desiccation of leaves and stems\", \"Premature senescence of plants\", \"Uneven plant health across the field with patches of greener plants\"]','Stressed',64,'Medium','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained, pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"West As