ad irrigation to prevent moisture on leaves, instead use drip irrigation to reduce humidity and prevent disease spread\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Apply copper-based fungicides\", \"Remove infected leaves and stems\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Implement fungicide spray schedule\", \"Monitor disease spread and adjust spray schedule as needed\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Maintain good air circulation and remove weeds\", \"Monitor plant health and adjust fertilizer application as needed\"], \"long_term\": [\"Develop a crop rotation plan to reduce disease risk\", \"Consider using resistant tomato varieties\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Monitor temperature and humidity levels to prevent disease spread\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Avoid spraying fungicides during high wind or rain to prevent drift and runoff\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Implement a 7-10 day fungicide spray schedule using copper-based products\", \"Step 2: Ensure good air circulation and remove weeds to reduce humidity and prevent disease spread\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Falling\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Wholesale Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"Optimal time to sell tomatoes is during the peak season (June-August)\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Expected price to decrease by 10-15% in the next 30 days due to oversupply\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Further disease spread and yield loss\", \"Risk 2: Reduced market price due to oversupply\"], \"crop_status\": \"Diseased\", \"health_score\": \"17.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Critical\", \"disease_status\": \"Late Blight\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The tomato crop is currently diseased with Late Blight, and the situation is critical. Immediate action is required to control the disease spread and prevent further yield loss. The farmer should implement a disease management plan, harvest 