e varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.029}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3504}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.369}]',28.6139,77.209,33.44,'completed','','2026-06-10 09:03:07.641295','2026-06-10 09:03:41.091544'),(40,'crop_images/eda259ecd3324b93817f4041b86e8da0.png','Wheat','None detected',85,'[\"Widespread chlorosis (yellowing) of foliage across large sections of the field\", \"Extensive necrosis (browning and drying) of foliage, particularly in distinct patches\", \"Uneven plant vigor, with some areas appearing greener and healthier compared to severely discolored areas\", \"General appearance of premature senescence or severe environmental stress\"]','Stressed',24,'Critical','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained, pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"West Asia and North Africa\", \"climate\": \"Temperate\", \"crop_name\": \"Wheat\", \"description\": \"Wheat is a staple food grain source for humans, grown on more land area than any other commercial crop. It is a cool-season crop with five principal classes, including hard red winter and hard red spring. Wheat is widely adapted to various environments, but optimal growth occurs in temperate climates with moderate water supply.\", \"growth_duration\": \"120-180 days\", 