eld loss if treatment is delayed.\", \"Pathogen transmission to neighboring crop blocks.\"], \"crop_status\": \"Diseased\", \"health_score\": \"39.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"High\", \"disease_status\": \"Septoria leaf spot\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The Tomato crop shows signs of Septoria leaf spot (Health Score: 39/100). Proper mitigation will prevent major yield loss.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Prune infected foliage.\", \"Implement a copper fungicide schedule.\", \"Improve field drainage.\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"23%\", \"wind_speed\": \"12.1 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"High moisture fosters fungal spore germination.\", \"Wind may spread pathogen spores to nearby plants.\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"Harvest during dry, sunny intervals.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Light Drizzle\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"Do not spray if rain is predicted in the next few hours.\", \"current_temperature\": \"42.0°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Optimize field drainage immediately.\", \"Spray only during low-wind mornings.\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Late Blight (Phytophthora infestans) is a devastating disease of tomato and potato. Symptoms include dark, water-soaked lesions on leaves and stems that rapidly expand. Management: Apply copper-based fungicides. Remove infected plants. Use resistant varieties. Avoid overhead irrigation.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"source\": \"plantvillage.psu.edu\", \"disease\": \"Late Blight\"}, \"relevance\": 1.0618}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.1464}, {\"content\": \"Tomato cultivation requires well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0–7.0. Scientific name: Solanum lycopersicum. Growth duration: 60–90 days after transplanting. NPK recommendation: 120:60:60 kg/ha. Requires staking for indeterminate varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2222}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2639}]',28.6139,77.209,10.88,'completed','','2026-06-10 09:14:45.390779','2026-06-10 09:14:56.276133'),(44,'crop_images/86d698f0e11d4f24b1beb1a4facda310.png','Wheat','Healthy',80,'[\"Yellowing and browning of leaves\", \"Dry and brittle texture\"]','Stressed',72,'Medium','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil, pH 6.0–7.0\", \"family\": \"N/A\", \"origin\": \"N/A\", \"climate\": \"Tropical/Subtropical\", \"crop_name\": \"Wheat\", \"description\": \"Wheat is an important agricultural crop grown worldwide.\", \"growth_duration\": \"60–120 days\", \"scientific_name\": \"Wheat spp.\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Pathogen infection under favorable conditions\"], \"symptoms\": [\"Visible damage associated with Healthy\"], \"treatment\": [\"Apply recommended fungicide/bactericide\", \"Remove infected plant material\"], \"prevention\": [\"Use certified disease-free seeds\", \"Practice crop rotation\"], \"precautions\": [\"Avoid overhead irrigation\", \"Sanitize pruning tools\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"Leaves\", \"Stems\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Spreads rapidly under cool and wet conditions.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Prune heavily damaged leaves\", \"Apply copper spray\"]}','{\"shelf_life\": \"7-14 days\", \"storage_type\": \"Cool, dry, ventilated store\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90%\", \