rop management practices\", \"Monitor for potential pests or diseases\", \"Maintain accurate crop records\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with moisture-resistant materials.\", \"shelf_life\": \"3-5 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags / Silos with controlled atmosphere\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Soybeans, as they can absorb moisture from Corn, and wheat, as they can be cross-contaminated with Corn dust.\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Maintain airtight conditions, avoid direct sunlight, and ensure regular cleaning and sanitation.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool to 15°C within 24 hours, grade and sort to remove damaged kernels, and wash to remove dirt and debris.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"6-8 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature and humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 300 kg/ha (150 kg/ha at sowing + 150 kg/ha at V6 stage)\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to environmental pollution and reduced soil fertility. Regular soil testing is recommended to avoid over-fertilization.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha (V6-V8 stage), 180:90:90 kg/ha (R1-R3 stage)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Nitrogen deficiency: Yellowing of leaves, reduced growth. Phosphorus deficiency: Purple or reddish discoloration of leaves, stunted growth. Potassium deficiency: Yellowing of lower leaves, stunted growth.\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at sowing, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Combine harvester\", \"harvest_duration\": \"90‑120 days after planting\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Mid‑morning to avoid heat stress\", \"equipment_required\"