ons\": [\"Isolate infected Wheat plants immediately to prevent disease transmission.\", \"Consult a local crop advisor for specific fungicide options.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Avoid overhead watering; use drip irrigation to prevent humidity buildup on leaves.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Scout fields and flag diseased crops.\", \"Apply immediate foliar sprays.\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Monitor disease spread.\", \"Sanitize tools daily.\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Assess fungicide efficacy.\", \"Adjust irrigation schedule.\"], \"long_term\": [\"Adopt crop rotation.\", \"Select disease-resistant seed varieties.\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Avoid spraying pesticides if rainfall is forecasted within 2-4 hours.\", \"High humidity increases disease spread risk; monitor crop health daily.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Prune and burn infected plant parts showing symptoms of Environmental stress.\", \"Improve space between plants to encourage air circulation.\", \"Apply general-purpose organic copper fungicide.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Mandi/District APMC Market\", \"Regional Wholesale Hub\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"Immediate post-drying stage\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹35-50/kg (local grade average)\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Slight upward trend in next 30 days due to localized crop supply drop.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Yield loss if treatment is delayed.\", \"Pathogen transmission to neighboring crop blocks.\"], \"crop_status\": \"Stressed\", \"health_score\": \"44.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"High\", \"disease_status\": \"Environmental stress\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The Wheat crop shows signs of Environmental stress (Health Score: 44/100). Proper mitigation will prevent major yield loss.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Prune infected foliage.\", \"Implement a copper fungicide schedule.\", \"Improve field drainage.\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"23%\", \"wind_speed\": \"14.5 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"High moisture fosters fungal spore germination.\", \"Wind may spread pathogen spores to nearby plants.\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"Harvest during dry, sunny intervals.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Clear Sky\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"Do not spray if rain is predicted in the next few hours.\", \"current_temperature\": \"41.3°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Optimize field drainage immediately.\", \"Spray only during low-wind mornings.\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Wheat (Triticum aestivum) cultivation: Sow in cool weather (10–25°C). Growth duration: 100–130 days. NPK: 120:60:40 kg/ha. Harvest when grain moisture is 14% or less. Store at <15°C in dry conditions.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 0.9806}, {\"content\": \"Powdery Mildew affects many crops including wheat, grapes, and cucurbits. White powdery coating appears on leaves and stems. Management: Apply sulfur-based fungicides. Improve air circulation. Avoid excess nitrogen fertilization.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Wheat\", \"source\": \"usda.gov\", \"disease\": \"Powdery Mildew\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2273}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2492}, {\"content\": \"Rice Blast (Pyricularia oryzae) is the most destructive rice disease globally. Symptoms: diamond-shaped lesions on leaves, neck rot at panicle. Management: Balanced nitrogen, silicon fertilization, fungicide sprays at boot stage.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Rice\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Rice Blast\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3664}]',28.6139,77.209,51.54,'completed','','2026-06-10 09:55:10.684549','2026-06-10 09:56:02.234896'),(51,'crop_images/74f989b530a449f4b98ec8d43906ffd7.jpg','Corn','Healthy',90,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil, pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"South America\", \"climate\": \"Warm temperate to tropical, 20-30°C\", \"crop_name\": \"Corn\", \"description\": \"Corn is an important cereal crop worldwide, providing food, feed, and industrial products. It is typically grown in well-drained soils with adequate moisture, and optimal yields are achieved with proper fertilization, irrigation, and pest management. Corn is a significant economic crop in many regions, with Africa producing 7.4% of the world\'s total in 2017. Its cultivation practices vary across different regions, but it is generally a high-yielding crop that requires careful management to maximize productivity.\", \"growth_duration\": \"70-120 days from sowing\", \"scientific_name\": \"Zea mays\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 400-600 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Sufficient water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced soil pH\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal leaf color and texture\", \"No visible lesions or necrosis\", \"No stunted growth or premature plant death\", \"Normal ear development and kernel size\"], \"treatment\": [\"No treatment necessary\", \"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor for potential pests or diseases\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain soil fertility and pH\", \"Provide adequate water supply\", \"Use crop rotation and sanitation practices\"], \"precautions\": [\"Avoid over-fertilization\", \"Monitor for potential pests or diseases\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"fruit\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy corn plants do not exhibit disease progression as they are not affected by any pathogens.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor plant health\", \"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Plan for future crop rotation\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates with airtight lids\", \"shelf_life\": \"3-5 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags / Controlled Atmosphere Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Other grains (e.g. wheat, rice), as they can absorb moisture and become moldy. Also, avoid storing near strong-smelling crops (e.g. onions, garlic) as corn can absorb odors.\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Low oxygen levels (0.5-1.5%), moderate temperature, and controlled humidity. Store in dark, well-ventilated area with regular sanitation.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool to 10-15°C within 24 hours of harvest, grade and sort to remove damaged kernels, and store in clean, dry hermetic bags.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Basal dose: 120 kg N + 60 kg P2O5 + 60 kg K2O per hectare. Top dressing: 60 kg N + 30 kg P2O5 + 30 kg K2O per hectare at 20 and 40 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to environmental pollution, soil degradation, and reduced crop yields. It is essential to conduct soil tests and adjust fertilizer application accordingly.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha (Basal dose) + 60:30:30 kg/ha (Top dressing at 20 DAT) + 60:30:30 kg/ha (Top dressing at 40 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Nitrogen deficiency: Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth. Phosphorus deficiency: Purple discoloration of leaves, stunted growth. Potassium deficiency: Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, increased susceptibility to disease.\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, top dressing at 20 and 40 DAT\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM (Farm Yard Manure) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP (Diammonium Phosphate) + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking, using a sharp knife or pruning shears to cut the ear from the plant\", \"harvest_duration\": \"65-90 DAT (Days After Transplanting)\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning, when the dew is still present, to minimize moisture loss and damage to the ears\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Sharp knife or pruning shears\", \"Harvest basket or container\", \"Measuring tape or ruler to check ear length and diameter\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit color change from green to yellow, orange, red, or a combination of these\", \"Firmness test: kernels should be firm and not soft to the touch\", \"Leaf senescence: lower leaves turn yellow and dry up\", \"Silking: tassels emerge and pollen is released\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss percentage: 5-10%, can be reduced by proper handling, storage, and transportation\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 7-10 days after pesticide application, to ensure the chemical has broken down and is no longer present on the crop\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Expected yield per hectare: 8-12 tonnes under good conditions, 4-6 tonnes under poor conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"June-August (Kharif season) / September-November (Rabi season)\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Overcast\", \"feels_like_c\": 41.5, \"temperature_c\": 40.7, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 15.8, \"humidity_percent\": 28, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0, \"wind_direction_deg\": 269, \"cloud_cover_percent\": 98}, \"latitude\": 20.5937, \"timezone\": \"Asia/Kolkata\", \"longitude\": 78.9629, \"fetched_at\": \"2026-06-10T10:02:42.691760Z\", \"forecast_7_days\": [{\"date\": \"2026-06-10\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 40.9, \"temp_min_c\": 32.1, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 22.2, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.3}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-11\", \"condition\": \"Partly Cloudy\", \"temp_max_c\": 41.0, \"t