ress.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check the irrigation system to ensure proper water supply\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizer as recommended\", \"Monitor the crop\'s response to the fertilizer application\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue to monitor the crop\'s health and take action as needed\", \"Prepare for harvest by checking the fruit color and kernel firmness\"], \"long_term\": [\"Plan for the next crop cycle, considering crop rotation and soil preparation\", \"Review and adjust the integrated pest management plan as needed\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Be prepared for potential heat stress and take measures to mitigate its effects, such as providing shade or using cooling systems.\", \"Monitor the weather forecast closely and be prepared for any sudden changes in weather conditions.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Maintain a strict crop rotation schedule to prevent the buildup of pathogens.\", \"Use resistant hybrids and apply triazole fungicides as needed, following integrated pest management principles.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"June-August (Kharif season) or September-November (Rabi season)\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"The price is expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with a potential for a slight increase during the peak harvest season.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Heat stress and drought due to the current weather conditions\", \"Potential for disease or pest outbreaks if the crop is not properly managed\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The corn crop is currently healthy, with a high health score and no visible symptoms of disease. However, the farmer should remain vigilant and take proactive measures to prevent potential risks, such as heat stress and drought, and to maintain optimal growing conditions. With proper management, the crop is expected to yield a high-quality harvest, and the farmer can take advantage of the stable market price to maximize their profits.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Monitor the crop closely and take action as needed to prevent disease or pest outbreaks\", \"Maintain proper irrigation and fertilization practices to promote healthy growth\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"28%\", \"wind_speed\": \"15.8 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Heat stress due to high temperature and low humidity\", \"Potential for drought if the dry weather conditions persist\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"The farmer should wait for the optimal harvest time, as the current weather conditions may not be favorable for harvest.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Overcast\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is not recommended to spray pesticides or fungicides today due to the high wind speed and potential for drift.\", \"current_temperature\": \"40.7°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Irrigate the crop regularly to prevent water stress\", \"Provide shade or use cooling systems to mitigate heat stress\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.0708}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.388}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.444}, {\"content\": \"Rice Blast (Pyricularia oryzae) is the most destructive rice disease globally. Symptoms: diamond-shaped lesions on leaves, neck rot at panicle. Management: Balanced nitrogen, silicon fertilization, fungicide sprays at boot stage.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Rice\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Rice Blast\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4514}]',20.5937,78.9629,59.05,'completed','','2026-06-10 10:02:13.192389','2026-06-10 10:03:12.245047'),(52,'crop_images/86cf894617dc487ea812cb1cd8ac988d.png','Wheat','None',85,'[\"Widespread foliar yellowing across large sections of the field\", \"Extensive foliar browning and drying, particularly in more severely affected patches\", \"Uneven plant development and color distribution, with some greener areas contrasting with discolored ones\", \"Overall appearance suggests premature senescence or severe environmental stress\"]','Stressed',72,'Medium','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy or clay-loam soil, pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Southwestern Asia and the Mediterranean region\", \"climate\": \"Temperate climate, 15-25°C\", \"crop_name\": \"Wheat\", \"description\": \"Wheat is a highly important crop globally, providing a staple food source for millions. It is typically grown in rotation with other crops to maintain soil fertility and reduce pests and diseases. Wheat cultivation involves careful planning of sowing, irrigation, and harvesting to ensure optimal yields and quality. The economic value of wheat lies in its versatility as a food ingredient, animal feed, and industrial raw material.\", \"growth_duration\": \"90-120 days from sowing\", \"scientific_name\": \"Triticum aestivum\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 400-600 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [], \"pathogen\": \"\", \"symptoms\": [], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Monitor crop health regularly\"], \"precautions\": [], \"disease_name\": \"None\", \"affected_areas\": [], \"disease_progression\": \"\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue with regular crop management practices\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with moisture-resistant paper\", \"shelf_life\": \"6-8 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"70-80% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Grains that are high in moisture (e.g., rice, corn) to prevent moisture transfer and mold growth. Also, avoid storing Wheat near strong-smelling crops (e.g., onions, garlic) to prevent flavor transfer.\", \"temperature_range\": \"5-10°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Maintain low temperature, moderate humidity, and minimal light exposure. Ensure good ventilation to prevent moisture accumulation.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool to 15°C within 24 hours of harvest. Grading and sorting should be done before storage. No washing is required.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature and humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total dosage: 250 kg/ha (DAP: 150 kg/ha, Urea: 100 kg/ha)\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid over-fertilization of Nitrogen, as it can lead to lodging and reduced grain quality\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha (Basal dose: 60:30:30 kg/ha, Top dressing: 60:30:30 kg/ha at 20 and 40 days after transplanting)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced grain yield\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at sowing, Top dressing at 20 