 growing conditions\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain good agricultural practices\", \"Monitor soil and water conditions regularly\", \"Ensure proper crop rotation\"], \"precautions\": [\"No specific precautions are required as the onions are healthy\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"bulb\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy onions do not progress or spread as they are disease-free.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor the onion crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Maintain good record-keeping of crop growth and development\", \"Plan for future crop rotations\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates with breathable materials\", \"shelf_life\": \"8-12 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes (due to risk of disease transmission); Onions with green shoots (due to potential for sprouting)\", \"temperature_range\": \"0-5°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation: minimal; Light: low; Sanitation: clean and dry storage area\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling: within 2 hours of harvest; Grading: by size and quality; Sorting: by color and shape; Washing: not recommended due to potential for water damage\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (e.g. high temperature, high humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 300 kg/ha (DAP 150 kg/ha + Urea 75 kg/ha + Zinc Sulphate 20 kg/ha + Boron 1.5 kg/ha + Manganese 10 kg/ha + FYM 25 t/ha (optional))\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid over-fertilization, as it can lead to bulb rot and reduced quality. Monitor soil pH and adjust fertilizer application accordingly.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha (basal), 75:37.5:37.5 kg/ha (top dressing at 20, 40, 60 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 20 kg/ha, Boron 1.5 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced bulb formation\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking with pruning shears\", \"harvest_duration\": \"60–90 days after transplanting\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning (6–10 AM) to reduce field heat and improve shelf life\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Pruning shears\", \"Clean plastic harvest crates\", \"Harvest apron/gloves\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit or grain reaches full size for the variety\", \"Color change to variety-specific mature color\", \"Skin becomes firm to gentle pressure\", \"Leaves begin to show natural senescence\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"15–25% typical losses; reduced by prompt cooling and careful handling\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"7–14 days after last pesticide application\", \"yield_considerations\": \"25–35 t/ha under good management; 10–15 t/ha under stress conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"Depends on planting date; typically 70–80 days from transplanting\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Clear Sky\", \"feels_like_c\": 39.7, \"temperature_c\": 36.5, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 13.8, \"humidity_percent\": 38, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0, \"wind_direction_deg\": 125, \"cloud_cover_percent\": 0}, \"latitude\": 28.6139, \"timezone\": \"Asia/Kolkata\", \"longitude\": 77.209, \"fetched_at\": \"2026-06-11T05:58:33.974047Z\", \"forecast_7_days\": [{\"date\": \"2026-06-11\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 38.5, \"temp_min_c\": 24.0, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 21.2, \"precipitation_mm\": 6.1}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-12\", \"condition\": \"Moderate Showers\", \"temp_max_c\": 31.8, \"temp_min_c\": 25.9, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 13.7, \"precipitation_mm\": 5.9}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-13\", \"condition\": \"Moderate Showers\", \"temp_max_c\": 34.7, \"temp_min_c\": 23.7, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 23.2, \"precipitation_mm\": 5.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-14\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 36.8, \"temp_min_c\": 27.3, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 9.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.3}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-15\", \"condition\": \"Overcast\", \"temp_max_c\": 38.8, \"temp_min_c\": 25.7, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 11.5, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-16\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 39.5, \"temp_min_c\": 28.4, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 9.5, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-17\", \"condition\": \"Clear Sky\", \"temp_max_c\": 40.4, \"temp_min_c\": 27.0, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 11.8, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0}], \"agricultural_advisory\": [\"? Low humidity: increase irrigation frequency.\"]}','{\"ai_advisory\": {\"harvest_advice\": \"Plan for harvest within the expected duration of 60–90 days after transplanting, looking for indicators such as full size for the variety, color change, and skin becoming firm.\", \"storage_advice\": \"Given the healthy state of the crop, follow the recommended storage conditions: Cold Storage at 0-5°C, 85-90% RH, with minimal ventilation, low light, and clean, dry sanitation to maintain quality and extend shelf life up to 8-12 weeks.\", \"fertilizer_advice\": \"Follow the recommended fertilizer application: DAP + Urea with an NPK ratio of 150:75:75 kg/ha (basal) and 75:37.5:37.5 kg/ha (top dressing at 20, 40, 60 DAT), including micronutrients like Zinc Sulphate, Boron, and Manganese as specified.\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pests, given the current healthy status and low severity.\", \"Immediate Action 2: Ensure proper irrigation management to prevent water stress, considering the current weather conditions.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Manage irrigation carefully to avoid water stress, considering the current temperature of 36.5°C and humidity of 38%. Ensure soil moisture levels are adequate without overwatering.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check irrigation systems to ensure proper water distribution\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizer as per the recommended schedule\", \"Continue monitoring for pests and diseases\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Implement IPM strategies as needed\", \"Maintain good agricultural practices\"], \"long_term\": [\"Plan for crop rotation to maintain soil health\", \"Consider resistant varieties for future plantings\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Be prepared for potential heat stress with temperatures at 36.5°C, ensuring adequate irrigation and possibly using shading techniques if necessary.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor for any changes in weather conditions that could lead to disease or pest issues, such as unexpected rainfall.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain good agricultural practices such as crop rotation, sanitation, and the use of resistant varieties to prevent disease onset.\", \"Step 2: Implement integrated pest management (IPM) principles, including cultural, biological, and chemical controls as necessary.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"Optimal time to sell onions is typically during the summer months when demand is higher\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, but this could change based on supply and demand factors.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Potential for disease or pest issues if good agricultural practices are not maintained\", \"Risk 2: Impact of weather extremes on crop health and yield\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The onion crop is currently in a healthy state with a high health score of 97.0/100 and no visible symptoms of disease. The urgency level is low, but it\'s crucial to continue monitoring the crop and adjusting management practices as needed to prevent any potential issues and ensure a successful harvest. By following the recommended advisory, including disease management, storage advice, irrigation, fertilizer application, and weather precautions, the farmer can optimize crop yield and quality.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue good agricultural practices to maintain crop health\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor weather conditions closely and adjust irrigation and other management practices as necessary\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"38%\", \"wind_speed\": \"13.8 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress due to high temperatures\", \"Risk 2: Potential for drought if no rainfall occurs in the near future\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"There is no immediate need to harvest early based on the current forecast, but continue to monitor weather conditions and crop maturity.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Clear Sky\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is relatively safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today due to low wind speed and no forecasted rainfall, but always follow label instructions and take necessary precautions.\", \"current_temperature\": \"36.5°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Irrigate carefully to avoid water stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor temperature and humidity levels closely for any changes\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3691}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4569}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.46}, {\"content\": \"Tomato cultivation requires well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0–7.0. Scientific name: Solanum lycopersicum. Growth duration: 60–90 days after transplanting. NPK recommendation: 120:60:60 kg/ha. Requires staking for indeterminate varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4829}]',28.6139,77.209,33.89,'completed','','2026-06-11 05:58:22.644203','2026-06-11 05:58:56.551208'),(68,'crop_images/fc2572b9e2e7407c8e5584ca5aff3c7c.png','Onion','Healthy',90,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained, fertile soil with pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Amaryllidaceae\", \"origin\": \"Central Asia, now widely cultivated in many parts of the world\", \"climate\": \"Temperate climate, 15-25°C\", \"crop_name\": \"Onion\", \"description\": \"Onion is a vital crop for human consumption, used in various forms such as fresh, dried, or processed. It is grown in many parts of the world, with major producers including China, India, and the United States. Onion cultivation practices involve careful selection of varieties, proper irrigation management, and pest and disease control. The crop is an essential source of income for many small-scale farmers and is valued for its nutritional and culinary benefits.\", \"growth_duration\": \"120-180 days from sowing\", \"scientific_name\": \"Allium cepa\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 400-600 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions for Onion\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Proper temperature and sunlight exposure\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal color and texture of Onion\", \"No visible signs of disease or pests\", \"Onion has a typical, well-formed shape and size\", \"No unusual growth patterns or deformities\"], \"treatment\": [\"No treatment required for Healthy Onion\", \"Continue to provide optimal growing conditions\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain proper soil pH and nutrient balance\", \"Ensure adequate water supply and drainage\", \"Monitor for pests and diseases that could impact Onion health\"], \"precautions\": [\"No specific safety precautions necessary for Healthy Onion\", \"Continue to follow standard agricultural safety protocols\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"fruit\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"No disease progression, Onion remains healthy and unaffected\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor Onion for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Maintain optimal growing conditions and provide necessary care\", \"Consider implementing integrated pest management (IPM) strategies\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates\", \"shelf_life\": \"8-12 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"80-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes, as they can cause sprouting in onions, and Apples, as they can cause ethylene production leading to spoilage\", \"temperature_range\": \"0-4°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation: minimal, Light: low, Sanitation: clean and dry storage area\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling: within 2 hours of harvest, Grading: by size and quality, Sorting: by color and shape, Washing: not recommended\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"1-2 weeks under poor conditions\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 300 kg/ha, Basal dose at transplanting (150 kg/ha), Top dressing at 20, 40, 60 DAT (75 kg/ha each)\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid over-fertilization with N, as it may lead to bulb splitting and reduced quality. Monitor soil pH and adjust fertilizer application accordingly.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 20 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, Reduced bulb formation, Delayed maturity\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, Top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha, Compost 15 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking\", \"harvest_duration\": \"60-80 DAT\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning or late afternoon to avoid heat stress and minimize moisture loss\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Gloves to protect hands from onion sap\", \"Sharp knife or onion puller to minimize damage to the bulb\", \"Tray or bag to collect harvested onions\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit color change from green to yellow or red\", \"Firmness test: Onions are ready to harvest when the neck is about 1 inch in diameter and the bulb is firm to the touch\", \"Leaf senescence: Onions are ready to harvest when the tops begin to yellow and fall over\", \"Bulb size: Onions are ready to harvest when they reach a diameter of 2-3 inches\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss percentage: 5-10%, can be reduced by storing onions in a cool, dry place with good ventilation\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 14 days after pesticide application to ensure the chemical has broken down to safe levels\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Expected yield per hectare: 20-30 tons under good conditi