h a temperature range of 0-4°C and humidity range of 80-90% RH to maintain quality and shelf life\", \"fertilizer_advice\": \"Apply the recommended fertilizer (DAP + Urea) at the specified dosage and timing to promote healthy growth and development\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Immediate Action 2: Ensure proper irrigation to prevent water stress\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Water the crop regularly, but avoid overwatering, which can lead to disease and pest issues, especially during hot and dry weather conditions\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check irrigation system\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizer as per recommended schedule\", \"Monitor crop growth and development\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue to monitor crop health and apply fungicides if necessary\", \"Prepare for harvest\"], \"long_term\": [\"Plan for crop rotation and soil conservation\", \"Consider integrated pest management strategies\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Protect the crop from extreme temperatures and heat stress\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Be prepared for potential rainfall and take necessary measures to prevent waterlogging\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain good crop hygiene and sanitation to prevent disease spread\", \"Step 2: Apply fungicides as a preventative measure if necessary, but currently not required due to healthy crop status\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market\", \"Wholesale Market\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"June-July for Kharif, October-November for Rabi\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Expected to remain stable in the next 30 days\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress and water stress due to high temperature and low humidity\", \"Risk 2: Potential for disease spread due to high temperature and low humidity\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The onion crop is currently healthy with a high health score, and the disease status is also healthy. However, the farmer should continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pests and ensure proper irrigation to prevent water stress. The weather forecast indicates a high temperature and low humidity, which may lead to heat stress and water stress, but the overall situation is under control, and the farmer can follow the recommended action plan to maintain a healthy and productive crop.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Recommendation 2: Ensure proper irrigation to prevent water stress\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"38%\", \"wind_speed\": \"13.8 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress and water stress due to high temperature and low humidity\", \"Risk 2: Potential for disease spread due to high temperature and low humidity\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"The farmer should wait for the optimal harvest time, around 60-80 days after transplanting, to ensure maximum yield and quality\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Clear Sky\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is not recommended to spray pesticides/fungicides today due to high wind speed and low humidity\", \"current_temperature\": \"36.5°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Provide shade for the crop during extreme heat\", \"Recommendation 2: Increase irrigation frequency to prevent water stress\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3691}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4569}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.46}, {\"content\": \"Tomato cultivation requires well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0–7.0. Scientific name: Solanum lycopersicum. Growth duration: 60–90 days after transplanting. NPK recommendation: 120:60:60 kg/ha. Requires staking for indeterminate varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4829}]',28.6139,77.209,38.11,'completed','','2026-06-11 05:59:45.344986','2026-06-11 06:00:23.457752'),(69,'crop_images/29bcb946b07a4665afaf8511b88776c7.png','Sugarcane','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil, pH 6.0-7.0, with adequate organic matter\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Southeast Asia\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C, high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for the production of sugar, ethanol, and other bio-products. It is typically cultivated using a ratoon crop system, where the same field is harvested multiple times from the same planting. Sugarcane is a labor-intensive crop that requires regular irrigation, fertilization, and pest management. The global sugarcane industry is valued at over $80 billion annually, with major producers including Brazil, India, and China.\", \"growth_duration\": \"12-18 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1200 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions for Sugarcane\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Effective crop management practices\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal green color and firm texture of the Sugarcane stalks\", \"Absence of visible signs of disease or pests\", \"No discoloration or lesions on the leaves or stalks\", \"Typical growth and development of Sugarcane plants\"], \"treatment\": [\"No treatment is necessary as the plants are healthy\", \"Monitoring for potential pests or diseases\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain good agricultural practices\", \"Monitor soil and water conditions\", \"Implement integrated pest management (IPM) strategies\"], \"precautions\": [\"Wear protective clothing and equipment when handling plants\", \"Avoid contamination of healthy plants with diseased ones\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy Sugarcane plants do not exhibit disease progression as they are free from pathogens and pests.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor the Sugarcane crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Maintain a record of crop health and management practices\", \"Consult with a plant pathologist or agricultural expert if any issues arise\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with moisture-resistant materials\", \"shelf_life\": \"6-8 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags or Silos with controlled ventilation\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Other sugarcane varieties to prevent cross-pollination and contamination, as well as crops with high moisture content (e.g., potatoes,