ed biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',28.6139,77.209,39.18,'completed','','2026-06-11 08:32:58.394376','2026-06-11 08:33:37.591077'),(70,'crop_images/751276755107454c8e07290de4aa65b7.jpg','Tobacco','Healthy',98,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0-7.0 and adequate organic matter\", \"family\": \"Solanaceae\", \"origin\": \"South America\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C with moderate humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Tobacco\", \"description\": \"Tobacco is an economically important crop for its production of nicotine, a key ingredient in various products. It is cultivated using a variety of practices, including rotation, irrigation, and fertilization. Tobacco is typically grown in large-scale commercial farms, with a significant portion being used for cigarette production. The global tobacco market is valued at billions of dollars annually, making it a vital crop for many economies.\", \"growth_duration\": \"70-90 days from transplanting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Nicotiana tabacum\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 400-600 mm per season with consistent moisture\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced soil pH and nutrient levels\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal leaf color and texture\", \"No visible signs of disease or pests\", \"No discoloration or lesions on leaves or stems\", \"Typical growth and development of tobacco plants\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor and control pests and diseases\", \"Implement integrated pest management (IPM) strategies\"], \"precautions\": [\"Avoid overwatering and nutrient overapplication\", \"Monitor soil pH and nutrient levels regularly\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Tobacco plants exhibit normal growth and development without any signs of disease progression.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Monitor tobacco plants regularly for signs of pests or diseases\", \"Maintain accurate records of crop growth and development\", \"Consult with agricultural experts for guidance on optimal growing conditions\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with paper or plastic to maintain humidity and prevent moisture accumulation\", \"shelf_life\": \"4-6 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags or Controlled Atmosphere Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Other crops that release ethylene gas, such as apples and bananas, as Tobacco is sensitive to ethylene\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Low light, moderate ventilation, and strict sanitation to prevent contamination and pest infestation\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling to 10-13°C, grading and sorting for quality, and washing to remove dirt and debris\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-3 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity, and poor ventilation)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 450 kg/ha (basal dose 225 kg/ha + top dressing 225 kg/ha)\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to reduced yield, increased risk of disease, and environmental pollution\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha (basal dose) + 75:37.5:37.5 kg/ha (top dressing at 20 DAT) + 75:37.5:37.5 kg/ha (top