des/fungicides today, considering the wind speed and lack of rainfall, but always follow label instructions and take necessary precautions.\", \"current_temperature\": \"25.0°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement irrigation to supplement natural rainfall\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor for pests and be prepared to apply control measures if necessary\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.1025}, {\"content\": \"Rice Blast (Pyricularia oryzae) is the most destructive rice disease globally. Symptoms: diamond-shaped lesions on leaves, neck rot at panicle. Management: Balanced nitrogen, silicon fertilization, fungicide sprays at boot stage.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Rice\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Rice Blast\"}, \"relevance\": 1.2561}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4211}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4872}]',28.6139,77.209,22.78,'completed','','2026-06-11 09:30:25.967681','2026-06-11 09:30:48.756546'),(76,'crop_images/72ddea12e81e44419db92e8cfe2f72a6.png','Sugarcane','Healthy',90,'[\"Uniformly green foliage\", \"Vigorous growth\", \"No visible lesions or spots\", \"No visible signs of wilting or nutrient deficiency\"]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil, pH 5.5-6.5 with adequate organic matter\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Southeast Asia and the Pacific Islands\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for sugar production and biofuel, cultivated in tropical and subtropical regions worldwide. It is typically planted in well-prepared fields with adequate irrigation and fertilization. Sugarcane is a perennial crop that requires careful management to optimize yields and minimize disease pressure. The global sugarcane industry generates significant economic value through sugar production and ethanol biofuel.\", \"growth_duration\": \"12-18 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1200 mm per season with adequate water supply\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced pH and nutrient levels\"], \"pathogen\": \"\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal green color of leaves\", \"No visible signs of disease or pests\", \"Sturdy and upright plant growth\", \"No premature ripening or senescence\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor and adjust nutrient and water supply\", \"Implement integrated pest management practices\"], \"precautions\": [\"Avoid overuse of fertilizers and pesticides\", \"Conduct regular soil and water testing\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"Leaf\", \"Stem\", \"Root\", \"Fruit\", \"Flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy Sugarcane does not spread; it is a stable and desirable state.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Monitor plant growth and adjust management practices as needed\", \"Maintain accurate records of crop management\", \"Consult with a qualified agricultural expert if concerns arise\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with plastic sheeting\", \"shelf_life\": \"6-8 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags or Silos with Controlled Atmosphere\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes, Onions, and Garlic due to risk of sprouting and ethylene production\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation: minimal, Light: low, Sanitation: clean and dry storage area\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling: 24-48 hours, Grading: by diameter and quality, Sorting: by color and freshness, Washing: not recommended due to risk of water damage\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"250 kg/hectare split across growing season\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid excess nitrogen which promotes soft growth susceptible to disease.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Borax 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing leaves (N), purple tints (P), brown leaf margins (K)\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast and incorporate into soil\", \"application_timing\": \"50% basal at planting; 25% at 30 DAT; 25% at 60 DAT\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"Farm Yard Manure (FYM) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 5 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"NPK Balanced Compound (19-19-19)\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Mechanical combine\", \"harvest_duration\": \"12-14 months\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning, when dew is still present, to minimize juice loss and ease harvesting\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Sugarcane harvester\", \"Juice extractor\", \"Baler\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"juice content > 15%\", \"brix value > 18%\", \"stalks turn yellow and becom