 in weather conditions that may impact crop quality or yield\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Partly Cloudy\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is not recommended to spray pesticides/fungicides today due to the high wind speed and low humidity, which may reduce efficacy and increase drift\", \"current_temperature\": \"39.7°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Irrigate the crop regularly to prevent water stress\", \"Monitor weather forecasts for any changes in temperature, humidity, or precipitation that may impact crop health\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4436}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',28.6139,77.209,39.52,'completed','','2026-06-11 11:42:19.612095','2026-06-11 11:42:59.142017'),(77,'crop_images/c7bc7748600c4c11b7e546f2021f92fd.png','Sugarcane','Healthy',95,'[\"Uniformly green foliage\", \"Vigorous growth\", \"No visible lesions or spots\", \"No signs of wilting or severe stress\"]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0-7.0 and adequate organic matter\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Southeast Asia\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for sugar production worldwide. It is cultivated in tropical and subtropical regions using a variety of practices, including monoculture and intercropping. Sugarcane is a significant source of income for many farmers and is used to produce sugar, ethanol, and other products. The crop requires careful management, including regular irrigation, fertilization, and pest control, to ensure optimal yields and quality.\", \"growth_duration\": \"9-12 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1200 mm per season\"}','{}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with moisture-resistant paper\", \"shelf_life\": \"4-6 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags or Silos with controlled ventilation\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Crops with high moisture content (e.g., potatoes, onions) to prevent moisture transfer and rot\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Dark, well-ventilated area, maintain cleanliness, avoid direct sunlight and heat sources\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling to 10-15°C, grading, sorting, and washing to remove dirt and debris\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-3 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity, and poor ventilation)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total: 300 kg N, 150 kg P2O5, 150 kg K2O per hectare. Split schedule: 150 kg N, 75 kg P2O5, 75 kg K2O at planting, 75 kg N, 37.5 kg P2O5, 37.5 kg K2O at 20 DAT, 75 kg N, 37.5 kg P2O5, 37.5 kg K2O at 40 DAT\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to soil salinization, water pollution, and reduced soil fertility. Regular soil testing is recommended to avoid over-fertilization.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha (at planting), 120:60:60 kg/ha (at 20 DAT), 90:45:45 kg/ha (at 40 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 5 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced sugar content, and lower yields\", \"application_method\": \"Drip fertigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at planting, top dressing at 20 and 40 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha, Compost 15 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Mechanical combine\", \"harvest_duration\": \"12-14 months from planting\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning when the temperature is between 15-25°C to minimize juice loss and reduce the risk of fungal diseases\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Sugarcane harvester\", \"Juice extractor\", \"Stalk cutter\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"juice content of 12-14% Brix\", \"firmness test (stalks should be firm and not easily crushed)\", \"leaf senescence (yellowing and drying of leaves)\", \"stalk diameter (should be at least 2.5 cm)\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss: 5-10% due to juice loss during transportation and storage, can be reduced by using airtight containers and minimizing handling\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 21 days after pesticide application to ensure the pesticide has degraded to a safe level\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Average yield: 60-80 tons per hectare under good c