 Onion is healthy\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor Onion for potential pests or diseases\", \"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Implement IPM strategies to prevent potential diseases\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with paper or polyethylene sheets\", \"shelf_life\": \"8-12 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"80-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes due to risk of disease transmission (e.g. scab), Onions should be stored separately to prevent moisture accumulation and sprouting\", \"temperature_range\": \"0-5°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation is not required, store in dark, maintain cleanliness and avoid moisture accumulation\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool to 10°C within 2 hours of harvest, grade and sort, wash with chlorinated water (50 ppm) for 10 minutes\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"1-2 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Basal dose: 400 kg/ha DAP + 200 kg/ha Urea, Top dressing: 200 kg/ha DAP + 100 kg/ha Urea, per hectare\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid over-fertilization, as it can lead to leaf burn and reduced bulb formation. Monitor soil pH and adjust fertilizer application accordingly.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha (basal dose) + 60:30:30 kg/ha (top dressing at 20, 40, 60 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Nitrogen deficiency: yellowing of leaves, Phosphorus deficiency: stunted growth, delayed maturity, Potassium deficiency: yellowing of leaves, marginal scorch\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation at transplanting, followed by drip fertigation at 20, 40, 60 DAT\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM (Farm Yard Manure) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DA