ions required\", \"Follow standard agricultural safety protocols\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy Sugarcane does not spread, it is a stable state\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Monitor Sugarcane regularly for signs of stress or disease\", \"Maintain accurate records of growth and development\", \"Implement integrated pest management strategies\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with plastic sheets to maintain humidity and prevent moisture accumulation.\", \"shelf_life\": \"4-6 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags or Silos with controlled ventilation\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Other sugarcane varieties, as cross-pollination can occur. Also, avoid storing with crops that are highly susceptible to pests and diseases, such as maize and sorghum.\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C (50-56°F)\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Dark, well-ventilated, and dry conditions to prevent moisture accumulation. Regular monitoring for pests and diseases.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling to 10-13°C (50-56°F) within 24 hours of harvest. Grading and sorting to remove damaged stalks. Washing is not recommended as it may lead to water spots.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity, and poor ventilation)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 350 kg N, 175 kg P2O5, 175 kg K2O per hectare, split into 3 applications\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to soil salinization, water pollution, and reduced soil fertility. Regular soil testing and monitoring of nutrient levels are essential to avoid over-fertilization risks.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha (at transplanting), 100:50:50 kg/ha (at 20 DAT), 50:25:25 kg/ha (at 40 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 20 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"N deficiency: Yellowing of older leaves, P def