ed humidity or rainfall.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain good agricultural practices such as crop rotation, sanitation, and the use of resistant varieties to prevent disease onset.\", \"Step 2: Implement Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles, including cultural, biological, and chemical controls as necessary.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"October-November for the Kharif season and January-February for the Rabi season\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹25-30/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with a potential slight increase during the peak harvest season.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress and drought due to current weather conditions\", \"Risk 2: Potential disease outbreak if good agricultural practices are not followed\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The sugarcane crop is currently in a healthy state with a high health score of 97.0/100. The key to maintaining this health status is to continue good agricultural practices, monitor the crop and weather closely, and adjust management strategies as necessary. With proper care and attention to potential risks such as heat stress and disease, the crop is expected to perform well and yield a good harvest.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue good agricultural practices to maintain crop health\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor weather and adjust irrigation and other management practices accordingly\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"36%\", \"wind_speed\": \"6.6 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress due to high temperatures\", \"Risk 2: Potential for drought if the dry spell continues\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"There is no immediate need to harvest early based on the current weather forecast.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Clear Sky\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today, considering the low wind speed and no forecasted rainfall.\", \"current_temperature\": \"35.3°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Increase irrigation frequency to mitigate heat stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor weather forecasts closely for any signs of rain to adjust irrigation schedules\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4436}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',28.6139,77.209,48.71,'completed','','2026-06-18 04:04:02.674426','2026-06-18 04:04:51.387958'),(87,'crop_images/d42e1b96033e42b48629f6addb957205.jpg','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',28.6139,77.209,NULL,'processing','','2026-06-18 06:32:52.122779','2026-06-18 06:32:52.122842'),(88,'crop_images/532c11a6fc914c7fa453af7e76213b9d.jpg','Onion','Healthy',98,'[\"No visible symptoms of disease, pest damage, or nutrient deficiency.\", \"Leaves are uniformly green, upright, and turgid.\", \"Bulbs appear firm, white, and free from lesions or discoloration.\", \"Roots are fibrous, well-developed, and show no signs of rot or damage.\"]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained, fertile soil with pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Amaryllidaceae\", \"origin\": \"Central Asia and the Mediterranean region\", \"climate\": \"Temperate climate with cool winters and warm summers, 15-25°C\", \"crop_name\": \"Onion\", \"description\": \"Onion is a cool-season crop that is widely cultivated for its edible bulbs. It is an important crop in many parts of the world, providing a source of income for millions of farmers. Onion cultivation practices include sowing seeds in well-prepared soil, followed by regular irrigation and fertilization. The crop is highly valued for its flavor, aroma, and medicinal properties, making it a staple ingredient in many cuisines.\", \"growth_duration\": \"120-150 days from sowing\", \"scientific_name\": \"Allium cepa\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 500-700 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Good soil quality\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal plant growth and development\", \"Green and firm leaves\", \"No signs of disease or pest damage\", \"Well-developed roots and bulbs\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor and control soil pH and nutrient levels\", \"Implement integrated pest management practices\"], \"precautions\": [\"Avoid overwatering and nutrient overapplication\", \"Monitor for potential disease outbreaks\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"bulb\"], \"disease_progression\": \"No disease progression occurs as the plant remains healthy.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor plant health and adjust growing conditions as needed\", \"Maintain good agricultural practices\", \"Consult with a plant pathologist or agricultural expert if concerns arise\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates with ventilation to prevent moisture accumulation\", \"shelf_life\": \"8-12 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"90-95% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes (due to risk of sprout induction and disease transmission); Onions and potatoes should not be stored in the same room due to potential for ethylene production and moisture accumulation\", \"temperature_range\": \"0-4°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation: minimal; Light: minimal; Sanitation: maintain cleanliness to prevent rot and mold growth\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling: 12-24 hours; Grading: by size and quality; Sorting: by size and quality; Washing: not recommended due to potential for bruising and moisture accumulation\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Basal dose: 150 kg/ha DAP + 75 kg/ha Urea at transplanting, Top dressing: 50 kg/ha DAP + 25 kg/ha Urea at 20 and 40 days after transplanting\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to excessive bulb size, reduced flavor, and increased risk of disease\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 20 kg/ha, Boron 1.5 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, and reduced bulb formation\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, Top dressing at 20 and 40 days after transplanting\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 20 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking\", \"harvest_duration\": \"120-150 DAT\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning when the soil is still moist to prevent damage to the bulbs\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Long-handled fork or cultivator for gently loosening the soil around the bulbs\", \"Gloves to protect hands from the sharp edges of the onions\", \"Twine or string for tying the onions into bundles\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Topsets begin to form a papery covering\", \"Onion bulbs are firm and have a dry, papery skin\", \"Leaves begin to yellow and die back\", \"Onion bulbs are fully formed and separated\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss percentage: 5-10%, can be reduced by proper curing and storage\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 14 days after pesticide application to ensure the chemicals have broken down to safe levels\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Expected yield per hectare: 15-20 tons for good conditions, 8-12 tons for poor conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"September-October for Rabi, March-April for Kharif\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Clear Sky\", \"feels_like_c\": 40.8, \"temperature_c\": 38.3, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 10.4, \"humidity_percent\": 28, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0, \"wind_direction_deg\": 281, \"cloud_cover_percent\": 16}, \"latitude\": 28.6139, \"timezone\": \"Asia/Kolkata\", \"longitude\": 77.209, \"fetched_at\": \"2026-06-18T06:37:24.609833Z\", \"forecast_7_days\": [{\"date\": \"2026-06-18\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 39.2, \"temp_min_c\": 29.4, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 12.8, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.1}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-19\", \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"temp_max_c\": 40.0, \"temp_min_c\": 30.1, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 14.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-20\", \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"temp_max_c\": 39.5, \"temp_min_c\": 30.5, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 15.9, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-21\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 39.8, \"temp_min_c\": 30.4, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 13.8, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-22\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 38.7, \"temp_min_c\": 28.5, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 12.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.5}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-23\", \"condition\": \"Clear Sky\", \"temp_max_c\": 39.0, \"temp_min_c\": 27.3, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 14.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-24\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 37.9, \"temp_min_c\": 29.3, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 13.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.6}], \"agricultural_advisory\": [\"⚠️ Extreme heat: irrigate crops early morning or evening.\", \"? Low humidity: increase irrigation frequency.\"]}','{\"ai_advisory\": {\"harvest_advice\": \"Harvest the onions when the tops begin to yellow and fall over, and the bulbs are firm and have a dry, papery skin.\", \"storage_advice\": \"Store the onions in a cool, dry place with minimal ventilation and light to maintain quality and shelf life.\", \"fertilizer_advice\": \"Apply the recommended fertilizer (DAP + Urea) at the specified dosage to promote healthy growth and development.\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pest damage.\", \"Immediate Action 2: Ensure proper irrigation to prevent water stress, considering the current high temperature and low humidity.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Irrigate the crop regularly, taking care not to overwater, which can lead to disease susceptibility.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the crop for any signs of disease or pest damage\", \"Apply irrigation as needed\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Continue to monitor the crop and apply fertilizer as recommended\", \"Maintain proper sanitation and crop rotation practices\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Monitor for signs of nutrient deficiency and adjust fertilizer application as needed\", \"Prepare for potential weather extremes\"], \"long_term\": [\"Plan for crop rotation and soil conservation practices\", \"Research and implement integrated pest management strategies\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Protect the crop from extreme temperatures and dry winds.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Be prepared for potential heat stress and take measures to mitigate its effects.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain good agricultural practices, including crop rotation and sanitation, to prevent disease onset.\", \"Step 2: Monitor the crop regularly for early detection of any disease symptoms.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"September-October for Rabi, March-April for Kharif\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"The price is expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with a potential increase during peak demand seasons.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress and drought due to high temperature and low humidity\", \"Risk 2: Potential for increased pest and disease pressure due to weather extremes\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The onion crop is currently healthy, with a high health score and no visible symptoms of disease or pest damage. However, the farmer should continue to monitor the crop and take proactive measures to mitigate potential risks, such as heat stress and drought, to ensure optimal growth and development. With proper care and management, the crop is expected to reach its full potential and yield a high-quality harvest.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement good agricultural practices, including crop rotation and sanitation, to prevent disease onset.\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor the crop regularly for early detection of any disease symptoms and adjust fertilizer application as needed.\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"28%\", \"wind_speed\": \"10.4 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress and drought due to high temperature and low humidity\", \"Risk 2: Potential for increased pest and disease pressure due to weather extremes\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"The farmer should wait to harvest until the optimal time, as indicated by the crop\'s physiological maturity and weather conditions.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Clear Sky\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is not recommended to spray pesticides/fungicides today due to the high wind speed and potential for drift.\", \"current_temperature\": \"38.3°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement irrigation scheduling to mitigate drought stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor weather forecasts and be prepared for potential extreme weather events\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3691}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4569}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.46}, {\"content\": \"Tomato cultivation requires well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0–7.0. Scientific name: Solanum lycopersicum. Growth duration: 60–90 days after transplanting. NPK recommendation: 120:60:60 kg/ha. Requires staking for indeterminate varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4829}]',28.6139,77.209,40.33,'completed','','2026-06-18 06:37:13.630546','2026-06-18 06:37:53.964851'),(89,'crop_images/9df5bc71ad884b0c884f23927b350ad2.jpg','Sugarcane','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil, pH 6.0-7.0, with adequate organic matter\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"South Asia and Southeast Asia\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C, with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for sugar production and biofuel. It is cultivated using a variety of practices, including monoculture, intercropping, and agroforestry. Sugarcane is a high-value crop, with global production valued at over $80 billion annually. Its cultivation supports the livelihoods of millions of farmers worldwide.\", \"growth_duration\": \"12-18 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1000 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced soil pH\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal green coloration of the leaves\", \"No visible signs of disease or pests\", \"Sturdy and upright plant growth\", \"No premature senescence or yellowing\"], \"treatment\": [\"No treatment is required as Healthy is a natural state of the plant\", \"Continue to provide optimal growing conditions\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor soil pH and adjust as necessary\", \"Ensure adequate water and nutrient supply\"], \"precautions\": [\"No specific safety precautions are required as Healthy is a natural state of the plant\", \"Continue to follow standard agricultural safety protocols\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy Sugarcane does not spread as it is a state of optimal growth and development.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor plant growth and development\", \"Maintain a clean and well-organized field\", \"Schedule regular soil testing and nutrient analysis\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with plastic to prevent moisture accumulation\", \"shelf_life\": \"6-8 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags or Silos with controlled ventilation\", \"humidity_range\": \"80-85% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes and Onions due to risk of sprout induction and ethylene production\", \"temperature_range\": \"12-15°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Maintain aeration to prevent CO2 buildup, store in a well-ventilated area, and keep away from direct sunlight\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool within 2 hours of harvest, grade and sort to remove damaged stalks, wash to remove dirt and debris\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Basal dose: 120 kg N, 60 kg P2O5, 60 kg K2O per hectare at transplanting. Top dressing: 30 kg N, 15 kg P2O5, 15 kg K2O per hectare at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting.\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to soil salinization, water pollution, and reduced soil fertility. Regular soil testing is recommended to avoid over-fertilization.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced sugar content\", \"application_method\": \"Drip fertigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking with pruning shears\", \"harvest_duration\": \"60–90 days after transplanting\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning (6–10 AM) to reduce field heat and improve shelf life\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Pruning shears\", \"Clean plastic harvest crates\", \"Harvest apron/gloves\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit or grain reaches full size for the variety\", \"Color change to variety-specific mature color\", \"Skin becomes firm to gentle pressure\", \"Leaves begin to show natural senescence\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"15–25% typical losses; reduced by prompt cooling and careful handling\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"7–14 days after last pesticide application\", \"yield_considerations\": \"25–35 t/ha under good management; 10–15 t/ha under stress conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"Depends on planting date; typically 70–80 days from transplanting\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"feels_like_c\": 32.0, \"temperature_c\": 31.7, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.9, \"humidity_percent\": 45, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0, \"wind_direction_deg\": 272, \"cloud_cover_percent\": 21}, \"latitude\": 18.506049, \"timezone\": \"Asia/Kolkata\", \"longitude\": 73.762003, \"fetched_at\": \"2026-06-18T10:37:42.696275Z\", \"forecast_7_days\": [{\"date\": \"2026-06-18\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 33.5, \"temp_min_c\": 23.2, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 19.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-19\", \"condition\": \"Lig