ons.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Manage irrigation carefully, considering the current dry weather conditions (0.0 mm rainfall) to prevent water stress, which could make the crop more susceptible to disease.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check irrigation systems\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply basal fertilizer dose if not already done\", \"Continue monitoring for disease and pests\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Consider top dressing with fertilizer\", \"Maintain good agricultural practices\"], \"long_term\": [\"Plan for crop rotation to maintain soil health\", \"Research resistant varieties for future planting\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Be prepared for potential heat stress with temperatures at 31.7°C, ensuring adequate irrigation.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor for any changes in weather conditions that could lead to disease susceptibility.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain good agricultural practices such as crop rotation, sanitation, and the use of resistant varieties to prevent disease onset.\", \"Step 2: Implement Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles, including cultural, biological, and chemical controls as necessary.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"Optimal time to sell sugarcane is typically during the peak harvest season\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹25-30/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with potential for slight increase during peak demand periods.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Drought or water stress due to lack of rainfall\", \"Risk 2: Potential for disease onset if good agricultural practices are not maintained\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The sugarcane crop is currently in a healthy state with a high health score of 97.0/100 and no visible symptoms of disease. The key to maintaining this status is to continue good agricultural practices, monitor weather conditions closely, and be prepared to adapt management strategies as necessary. With proper care and attention, the crop is expected to reach its full potential and yield a successful harvest.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue monitoring the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Recommendation 2: Maintain proper irrigation and fertilizer management\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"45%\", \"wind_speed\": \"18.9 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress due to high temperatures\", \"Risk 2: Potential for drought if dry conditions persist\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"There is no immediate need to harvest early based on the current weather forecast.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Mainly Clear\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today, considering the low wind speed and no rainfall forecast.\", \"current_temperature\": \"31.7°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Increase irrigation frequency to mitigate heat stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor weather forecasts closely for any changes\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4436}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',18.506049,73.762003,45.84,'completed','','2026-06-18 10:37:31.189351','2026-06-18 10:38:17.039364'),(90,'crop_images/02beb5b0c29048e9b0e8d76d2bf7b94d.jpg','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',18.506049,73.762003,NULL,'processing','','2026-06-18 10:40:20.546996','2026-06-18 10:40:20.547034'),(91,'crop_images/68694bbfb4fd4b2295586b24461bb9cb.jpg','Corn','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy or sandy loam soil, pH 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Central America and Mexico\", \"climate\": \"Warm temperate to tropical, 20-30°C\", \"crop_name\": \"Corn\", \"description\": \"Corn is a staple crop globally, providing food, feed, and industrial products. It is typically grown in well-drained soils with adequate moisture, using conservation tillage and crop rotation practices to maintain soil health. Corn is a significant economic crop, with the global market valued at over $200 billion annually. Its cultivation requires careful management of pests, diseases, and nutrient deficiencies to ensure optimal yields.\", \"growth_duration\": \"70-120 days from sowing\", \"scientific_name\": \"Zea mays\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 400-600 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced soil pH\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal green color of leaves\", \"Well-developed root system\", \"Strong stem growth\", \"Abundant ear formation\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal soil fertility\", \"Provide adequate water supply\", \"Control weeds and pests\"], \"precautions\": [\"Monitor for signs of disease in neighboring fields\", \"Avoid overuse of fertilizers and pesticides\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"fruit\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy corn plants exhibit optimal growth and development through the entire growth cycle.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue regular crop management practices\", \"Monitor for signs of stress or disease\", \"Maintain accurate field records\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates to allow for airflow and moisture control.\", \"shelf_life\": \"4-6 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Dry Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"60-70% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Other grains (e.g., wheat, oats) to prevent cross-contamination and moisture absorption.\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Well-ventilated, low light, and clean storage area. Avoid direct sunlight and moisture.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling to 10°C, grading, sorting, and washing before storage. Dry the ears thoroughly before storage.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-3 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature and humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 300-400 kg/ha, split into 2-3 applications: 150-200 kg/ha at sowing, 100-150 kg/ha at 20-25 days after sowing, 50-100 kg/ha at 40-45 days after sowing\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to soil pollution, water pollution, and reduced soil fertility. Regular soil testing is recommended to avoid over-fertilization.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/hectare for vegetative stage, 180:90:90 kg/hectare for reproductive stage\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced ear formation, and kernel size\", \"application_method\": \"Broadcast + incorporation, followed by irrigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at sowing, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM (Farm Yard Manure) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha, Compost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP (Diammonium Phosphate) + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Mechanical combine\", \"harvest_duration\": \"60-80 days after sowing (DAT)\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning, when dew is still present, to minimize moisture loss and reduce shattering\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Combine harvester\", \"Corn header\", \"Grain cart or trailer\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit color change from green to yellow, orange, or red\", \"Firmness test: kernels should be hard and difficult to dent\", \"Leaf senescence: leaves turn yellow and dry\", \"Moisture content: 20-25% for dry corn\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss: 2-5%, can be reduced by proper drying, storage, and handling\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 14 days after pesticide application, to ensure the pesticide has degraded to safe levels\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Expected yield: 8-10 tons per hectare under good conditions, 4-6 tons per hectare under poor conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"October-November for Kharif, March-April for Rabi\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"feels_like_c\": 32.0, \"temperature_c\": 31.7, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.9, \"hum