ealth\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.0708}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.388}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.444}, {\"content\": \"Rice Blast (Pyricularia oryzae) is the most destructive rice disease globally. Symptoms: diamond-shaped lesions on leaves, neck rot at panicle. Management: Balanced nitrogen, silicon fertilization, fungicide sprays at boot stage.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Rice\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Rice Blast\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4514}]',18.506037,73.761961,40.08,'completed','','2026-06-18 10:44:48.218298','2026-06-18 10:45:28.307125'),(92,'crop_images/344db30723b74c72a043479f129b6e6e.jpg','Sugarcane','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil with a pH of 6.0-7.0\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"South Asia and Southeast Asia\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for the production of sugar and biofuels. It is typically cultivated using a system of planting, harvesting, and replanting, with multiple harvests per year. Sugarcane cultivation requires careful management of soil, water, and pests to maximize yields and minimize environmental impact. The economic value of sugarcane lies in its ability to produce high-quality sugar and ethanol, making it a crucial crop for many countries.\", \"growth_duration\": \"12-18 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1200 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced soil pH\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal green color of leaves\", \"No visible lesions or discoloration\", \"No stunted growth or reduced yield\", \"No signs of stress or disease\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor and adjust nutrient and water supply\", \"Regularly inspect for signs of stress or disease\"], \"precautions\": [\"No specific precautions necessary, as it is a healthy state\", \"Continue with regular farm practices\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"fruit\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"No progression or spread, as it is a healthy state\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue monitoring for signs of stress or disease\", \"Maintain regular farm practices\", \"No immediate action necessary\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates with a breathable lining\", \"shelf_life\": \"4-6 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes, Onions, and other high-sulfur crops due to risk of off-flavors and contamination\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation: moderate, Light: minimal, Sanitation: regular cleaning and fumigation to control pests and diseases\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling: within 24 hours, Grading: by quality and size, Sorting: by color and freshness, Washing: not recommended due to risk of water damage\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-3 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature, high humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 220 kg/ha (120 kg/ha at transplanting, 50 kg/ha at 20 DAT, 50 kg/ha at 40 DAT)\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid over-fertilization, especially with NPK, to prevent environmental pollution and soil degradation\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced sugar content\", \"application_method\": \"Drip fertigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP 120 kg/ha + Urea 100 kg/ha\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Mechanical combine or manual hand-picking\", \"harvest_duration\": \"180-200 DAT\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning or late afternoon to avoid heat stress and minimize juice loss\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Sugarcane harvester\", \"Juicer or crusher\", \"Tractor or forklift for transportation\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Brix value of 12-15\", \"Fruit stalk diameter of 2.5-3.5 cm\", \"Leaf senescence and yellowing\", \"Fruit stalk color change to yellow or brown\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss: 5-10%, can be reduced by proper handling, drying, and storage\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"14-21 days after pesticide application\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Expected yield: 60-80 tons/hectare under good conditions, 40-60 tons/hectare under poor conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"November-December\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"feels_like_c\":