er application plan, including DAP 120 kg/ha + Urea 100 kg/ha, to support the crop\'s nutritional needs.\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pests, given the current healthy status and low severity.\", \"Immediate Action 2: Ensure proper irrigation management to prevent water stress, considering the current weather conditions with no rainfall.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Manage irrigation carefully, considering the current temperature and humidity levels, to prevent water stress and promote healthy growth.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Monitor crop health\", \"Check irrigation system\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizers as scheduled\", \"Inspect for pests or diseases\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue monitoring and maintenance\", \"Plan for harvest preparations\"], \"long_term\": [\"Review and adjust crop management plan as necessary\", \"Consider soil health and rotation for future crops\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Be prepared for potential heat stress with temperatures at 31.3°C, ensuring adequate irrigation.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor for any changes in weather conditions that could lead to disease onset or pest infestation.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Implement Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles, including cultural control, biological control, and chemical control as needed.\", \"Step 2: Maintain sanitation, use resistant varieties, and practice crop rotation to prevent disease onset.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"November to December, aligning with the expected harvest period\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹25-30/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with potential for slight increase during peak harvest season.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Potential disease onset due to changes in weather conditions\", \"Risk 2: Heat stress affecting crop health and yield\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The sugarcane crop is currently in a healthy state with a high health score, and the disease status is healthy. The farmer should continue to monitor the crop and weather conditions, follow the recommended management plan, and be prepared for any potential risks such as disease onset or heat stress. With proper care and management, the crop is expected to reach its full potential and yield a good harvest.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue monitoring crop health and weather conditions closely\", \"Recommendation 2: Follow the recommended fertilizer and irrigation plan to support crop growth\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"47%\", \"wind_speed\": \"18.9 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress due to high temperatures\", \"Risk 2: Potential for drought if no rainfall occurs\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"There is no immediate need to harvest early based on the current forecast, but continue to monitor the crop and weather conditions.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Mainly Clear\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today, given the mainly clear conditions and moderate wind speed.\", \"current_temperature\": \"31.3°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Increase irrigation frequency to mitigate heat stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Monitor weather forecasts closely for any changes\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4436}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',18.506052,73.762026,42.57,'completed','','2026-06-18 10:51:54.592058','2026-06-18 10:52:37.172789'),(93,'crop_images/5852218444a340948bfd7c71c99b6bd8.jpg','Tobacco','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0-7.0, high organic matter content\", \"family\": \"Solanaceae\", \"origin\": \"South America, specifically the Andean region\", \"climate\": \"Warm temperate to tropical, 15-25°C with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Tobacco\", \"description\": \"Tobacco is an important cash crop globally, with significant economic value. It is cultivated for its leaves, which are used to produce cigarettes, cigars, and other tobacco products. Tobacco cultivation requires careful management, including crop rotation, fertilization, and pest control to maintain soil health and prevent disease. The crop is often grown in greenhouses or under shade to control temperature and humidity.\", \"growth_duration\": \"120-150 days from transplanting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Nicotiana tabacum\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate to high, 800-1000 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions for Tobacco\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced pH levels in the soil\"], \"pathogen\": \"\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal plant growth and development\", \"Green and healthy leaves\", \"No visible signs of disease or stress\", \"Normal root development\"], \"treatment\": [\"No treatment is required for Healthy Tobacco plants\", \"Continue to provide optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor for any signs of disease or stress\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions for Tobacco\", \"Monitor soil pH levels and adjust as necessary\", \"Ensure adequate water and nutrient supply\"], \"precautions\": [\"No specific safety precautions are required for Healthy Tobacco plants\", \"Continue to follow standard agricultural safety protocols\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy Tobacco plants continue to grow and develop without any signs of disease or stress.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor plant growth and development\", \"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Schedule regular soil tests to ensure balanced pH levels\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with paper to maintain humidity and prevent moisture buildup.\", \"shelf_life\": \"4-6 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes, Onions, and other high-moisture crops due to risk of moisture transfer and mold growth.\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Maintain 50-60% ventilation, store in dark, and ensure good sanitation to prevent mold growth.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool to 15°C within 2 hours of harvest, grade and sort by size and quality, and wash to remove dirt and debris.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-4 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature and humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total: 300 kg/ha (DAP 150 kg/ha + Urea 150 kg/ha), split into 3 applications: 100 kg/ha at transplanting, 100 kg/ha at 20 DAT, 100 kg/ha at 40 DAT\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to leaf burn, reduced yields, and environmental pollution. Regular soil testing and monitoring of nutrient levels are essential to avoid over-fertilization.\", \"npk_ratio\": \"150:75:75 kg/ha (basal dose), 100:50:50 kg/ha (top dressing at 20 DAT), 50:25:25 kg/ha (top dressing at 40 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 20 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Nitrogen deficiency: Yellowing of lower leaves, stunted growth. Phosphorus deficiency: Purpling of leaves, stunted growth. Potassium deficiency: Yellowing of older leaves, stunted growth. Zinc deficiency: Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth. Boron deficiency: Distortion of leaves, stunted growth.\", \"application_method\": \"Drip fertigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, top dressing at 20 and 40 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM (Farm Yard Manure) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP (18-46-0) + Urea (46-0-0)\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking\", \"harvest_duration\": \"120-140 DAT\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning when dew is still present to prevent leaf damage and improve curing\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Ladders or step stools for safe access to plants\", \"Pruning shears for cutting the stalks\", \"Bags or containers for collecting the harvested leaves\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"change in leaf 