ditions.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Manage irrigation carefully, avoiding overwatering which can lead to disease susceptibility, especially under the current dry and clear weather conditions.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the crop for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check irrigation systems for proper functioning\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizer as per the recommended schedule\", \"Monitor weather forecasts for any changes\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue crop monitoring and maintain good agricultural practices\", \"Plan for potential pest management strategies\"], \"long_term\": [\"Review and adjust the crop management plan as necessary based on crop development and weather conditions\", \"Prepare for harvest and post-harvest handling\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Be prepared for potential drought stress due to the current low rainfall.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor for high-temperature stress, which can impact sugarcane growth and productivity.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain good agricultural practices such as crop rotation, sanitation, and the use of resistant varieties to prevent disease onset.\", \"Step 2: Implement Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles, including cultural, biological, and chemical controls as needed.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"February-March for optimal prices\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹25-30/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with a potential slight increase during peak demand seasons.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Potential disease onset if good agricultural practices are not maintained\", \"Risk 2: Weather-related stresses such as drought or high temperatures\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The sugarcane crop is currently in a healthy state with a high health score, indicating minimal immediate risks. However, continuous monitoring and adherence to good agricultural practices are crucial to prevent disease onset and manage potential weather-related stresses. By following the recommended action plan and staying informed about weather and market trends, the farmer can optimize crop yield and profitability.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue monitoring the crop and maintain good agricultural practices\", \"Recommendation 2: Be prepared to adjust the management plan based on weather forecasts and crop development\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"47%\", \"wind_speed\": \"19.0 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Drought stress due to low rainfall\", \"Risk 2: High-temperature stress impacting growth\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"There is no immediate need to harvest early based on the current weather forecast.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Mainly Clear\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is relatively safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today, given the low wind speed and no rainfall forecast.\", \"current_temperature\": \"30.9°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement efficient irrigation practices to mitigate drought stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Consider using shading or cooling methods to reduce high-temperature stress\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4436}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',18.506086,73.762144,13.44,'completed','','2026-06-18 11:26:25.973481','2026-06-18 11:26:39.417161'),(96,'crop_images/2357d6ddbb11412f90399fe615d454bd.jpg','Sugarcane','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil, pH 6.0-7.0, with adequate nutrient supply\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"Southeast Asia\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C, with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for sugar production and biofuel, cultivated in tropical and subtropical regions worldwide. It is typically grown from sets or seedlings, and requires careful management of soil, water, and pests to optimize yield. Sugarcane is a significant economic crop, providing income for millions of farmers and supporting local economies. Its cultivation practices involve mulching, irrigation, and fertilization to promote healthy growth and high sugar content.\", \"growth_duration\": \"12-18 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1200 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"No stress factors such as pests or diseases\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal color and texture of leaves\", \"No visible lesions or spots\", \"No signs of wilting or yellowing\", \"Normal growth rate\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor for signs of stress or disease\", \"Implement integrated pest management practices\"], \"precautions\": [], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\"], \"disease_progression\": \"No progression, as Healthy is a state of optimal health\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Monitor Sugarcane regularly for signs of disease or stress\", \"Maintain accurate records of growth and development\", \"Consult with a plant pathologist or agricultural expert if concerns arise\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with plastic sheets to maintain humidity and prevent moisture from entering the bags.\", \"shelf_life\": \"6-8 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes, as they can cause the sugarcane to sprout. Also, avoid storing sugarcane near strong-smelling crops, as it can absorb odors.\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Store in a cool, dry, and well-ventilated area. Avoid direct sunlight and moisture.\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cool to 10-13°C within 2 hours of harvest. Grading and sorting should be done within 24 hours. Washing is not recommended as it can cause damage to the sugarcane.\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-3 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature and humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Basal dose: 1