r global food security, providing essential nutrients and flavor to various cuisines. It is typically grown from seed or sets, requiring careful management of soil fertility, irrigation, and pest control. Onion cultivation practices vary depending on the region and market demand, with some farmers using intensive methods to increase yields and others adopting more sustainable approaches. The global onion market is valued at billions of dollars, with India being the largest producer and exporter.\", \"growth_duration\": \"120-180 days from seed sowing\", \"scientific_name\": \"Allium cepa\", \"water_requirement\": \"Moderate, 400-600 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced pH levels\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal growth and development\", \"No visible signs of disease\", \"No discoloration or lesions\", \"No abnormal growth patterns\"], \"treatment\": [], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor and adjust nutrient and water supply\", \"Regularly inspect for signs of disease\"], \"precautions\": [\"Use personal protective equipment when handling plants\", \"Avoid contamination of healthy plants\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\", \"fruit\", \"flower\"], \"disease_progression\": \"No disease progression, as Healthy is a state of optimal growth and development.\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor and maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Adjust nutrient and water supply as needed\", \"Inspect for signs of disease regularly\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with paper or straw\", \"shelf_life\": \"8-12 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Cold Storage\", \"humidity_range\": \"80-85% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Potatoes, as they can cause sprouting and rot in onions, and Onions can also cause moisture to accumulate in potato storage\", \"temperature_range\": \"0-5°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Ventilation: minimal, Light: low, Sanitation: clean and dry storage area\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling: within 2 hours of harvest, Grading: based on size and quality, Sorting: by size and quality, Washing: not recommended\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"1-2 weeks under poor conditions\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Basal dose: 400 kg/ha DAP + 200 kg/ha Urea, Top dressing: 200 kg/ha DAP + 100 kg/ha Urea (split over 20 and 40 DAT)\", \"cautions\": \"Over-fertilization can lead to onion bulb splitting and reduced flavor, Avoid excessive application of nitrogen to prevent leaf growth at the expense of bulb formation\", \"npk_ratio\": \"120:60:60 kg/ha (basal dose) + 60:30:30 kg/ha (top dressing at 20 and 40 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Nitrogen deficiency: Yellowing of leaves, Phosphorus deficiency: Stunted growth, Potassium deficiency: Leaf scorch\", \"application_method\": \"Drip fertigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at transplanting, Top dressing at 20 and 40 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM (Farm Yard Manure) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP (Di-Ammonium Phosphate) + Urea\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Manual hand-picking\", \"harvest_duration\": \"120-150 DAT\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning when the dew is still present, as it helps in easy separation of onions from the soil\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Sharp sickle or a knife for cutting the onion neck\", \"Rake or a fork for gently lifting the onions\", \"Tray or a container for collecting the harvested onions\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit color change from green to yellow or brown\", \"Firmness test using a pressure gauge\", \"Leaf senescence and yellowing\", \"Onion neck diameter reaches 1.5-2.5 cm\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss: 5-10%, can be reduced by proper curing, drying, and storage\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 14 days after pesticide application, to ensure the chemical has dissipated and is safe for consumption\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Expected yield: 25-30 tons per hectare under good conditions, 15-20 tons per hectare under poor conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"September-October for Rabi, March-April for Kharif\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"feels_like_c\": 30.9, \"temperature_c\": 30.7, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.7, \"humidity_percent\": 47, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0, \"wind_direction_deg\": 272, \"cloud_cover_percent\": 25}, \"latitude\": 18.506084, \"timezone\": \"Asia/Kolkata\", \"longitude\": 73.762169, \"fetched_at\": \"2026-06-18T11:39:32.186330Z\", \"forecast_7_days\": [{\"date\": \"2026-06-18\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 33.5, \"temp_min_c\": 23.2, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 19.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-19\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 34.2, \"temp_min_c\": 22.0, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 17.5, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.3}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-20\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 33.9, \"temp_min_c\": 23.0, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 3.5}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-21\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 32.5, \"temp_min_c\": 23.8, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.7, \"precipitation_mm\": 6.7}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-22\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 30.7, \"temp_min_c\": 23.5, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 14.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 10.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-23\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm with Hail\", \"temp_max_c\": 25.5, \"temp_min_c\": 22.9, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 16.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 12.3}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-24\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 27.1, \"temp_min_c\": 22.1, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 19.5, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.8}], \"agricultural_advisory\": [\"✅ Weather conditions are favourable for crop growth.\"]}','{\"ai_advisory\": {\"harvest_advice\": \"Plan for harvest based on the expected duration and indicators such as fruit color change, firmness, and leaf senescence.\", \"storage_advice\": \"Given the healthy state of the crop, store onions in a cool, dry place with minimal ventilation and low light to maintain quality and prolong shelf life.\", \"fertilizer_advice\": \"Continue with the recommended fertilizer application plan, including DAP and Urea, to support healthy plant growth and development.\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of disease or pests, given the current healthy status and low severity.\", \"Immediate Action 2: Ensure proper irrigation management to prevent water stress, considering the current weather conditions.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Water management should focus on maintaining optimal soil moisture levels without overwatering, which can lead to disease susceptibility.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the field for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check irrigation systems\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizer as per the recommended schedule\", \"Monitor weather forecasts\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue with IPM practices\", \"Plan for harvest preparations\"], \"long_term\": [\"Review and adjust the crop rotation plan\", \"Consider implementing new technologies for disease management\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Be prepared for potential heat stress with the current high temperature.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor for any changes in weather conditions that could lead to disease susceptibility.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain a clean and dry field to prevent the spread of potential diseases.\", \"Step 2: Implement integrated pest management (IPM) principles, including cultural control, resistant varieties, and biological control methods.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market A\", \"Regional Market B\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"Optimal time to sell onions is during the peak demand seasons, typically after the harvest period.\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹40-50/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with potential for slight increase during peak demand periods.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Potential for disease outbreak if field conditions become favorable\", \"Risk 2: Impact of weather extremes on crop health and yield\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The onion crop is currently in a healthy state with a low disease severity and high health score. Continuing with integrated pest management practices, proper irrigation, and fertilizer application will be crucial in maintaining the health of the crop. Monitoring weather conditions and being prepared for potential risks will also help in ensuring a successful harvest. With stable market prices and moderate demand, planning for the best selling time and considering nearby markets will be important for maximizing returns.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue with proactive disease management and monitoring\", \"Recommendation 2: Adjust irrigation and fertilizer application based on weather and crop conditions\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"47%\", \"wind_speed\": \"18.7 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress due to high temperatures\", \"Risk 2: Potential for drought if rainfall remains low\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"There is no immediate need to harvest early based on the current weather forecast.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Mainly Clear\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is safe to spray pesticides/fungicides today, considering the low wind speed and no rainfall forecast.\", \"current_temperature\": \"30.7°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement irrigation scheduling to mitigate drought risk\", \"Recommendation 2: Consider using shade cloth or other methods to reduce heat stress\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3691}, {\"content\": \"General crop storage principles: Temperature and humidity control are critical. Most vegetables: 0–10°C, 85–95% RH. Grains: <15°C, <14% moisture. Fruits: 10–15°C, 85–90% RH. Use hermetic bags or cold rooms to extend shelf life.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"storage\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4569}, {\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.46}, {\"content\": \"Tomato cultivation requires well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0–7.0. Scientific name: Solanum lycopersicum. Growth duration: 60–90 days after transplanting. NPK recommendation: 120:60:60 kg/ha. Requires staking for indeterminate varieties.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Tomato\", \"type\": \"overview\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4829}]',18.506084,73.762169,25.87,'completed','','2026-06-18 11:49:12.924602','2026-06-18 11:49:38.804129'),(99,'crop_images/a5862b6d7348478a9843eb92e4409cd9.jpg','Sugarcane','Healthy',95,'[]','Healthy',97,'Low','{\"soil\": \"Well-drained loamy soil with pH 6.0-7.0 and adequate organic matter\", \"family\": \"Poaceae\", \"origin\": \"South Asia and Southeast Asia\", \"climate\": \"Warm tropical, 20-30°C with high humidity\", \"crop_name\": \"Sugarcane\", \"description\": \"Sugarcane is a highly important crop for sugar production, accounting for over 70% of global sugar production. It is cultivated in tropical and subtropical regions worldwide, with major producers including Brazil, India, and China. Sugarcane cultivation involves planting sets or seedlings in well-prepared soil, followed by regular irrigation and fertilization. The crop is harvested after 12-14 months, with the harvested canes then processed to extract sugar and other by-products.\", \"growth_duration\": \"12-14 months from planting\", \"scientific_name\": \"Saccharum officinarum\", \"water_requirement\": \"High, 800-1000 mm per season\"}','{\"causes\": [\"Optimal growing conditions\", \"Adequate water and nutrient supply\", \"Balanced soil pH\"], \"pathogen\": \"None\", \"symptoms\": [\"Normal green color and turgid appearance of leaves\", \"Absence of visible lesions or discoloration\", \"Sturdy and upright plant growth\", \"No visible signs of stress or disease\"], \"treatment\": [\"No treatment is required for Healthy Sugarcane\", \"Continue with regular crop management practices\"], \"prevention\": [\"Maintain optimal growing conditions\", \"Monitor soil pH and adjust as necessary\", \"Ensure adequate water and nutrient supply\"], \"precautions\": [\"No specific safety precautions are required for Healthy Sugarcane\", \"Continue with standard field safety protocols\"], \"disease_name\": \"Healthy\", \"affected_areas\": [\"leaf\", \"stem\", \"root\"], \"disease_progression\": \"Healthy Sugarcane does not spread through any disease mechanism\", \"recommended_actions\": [\"Continue to monitor the crop for any signs of stress or disease\", \"Maintain regular crop management practices\", \"Consider conducting a soil test to ensure optimal growing conditions\"]}','{\"packaging\": \"Perforated polyethylene bags or wooden crates lined with moisture-resistant materials\", \"shelf_life\": \"6-8 weeks\", \"storage_type\": \"Hermetic Bags / Silos with controlled ventilation\", \"humidity_range\": \"85-90% RH\", \"do_not_store_with\": \"Other high-moisture crops like potatoes and carrots to prevent moisture transfer and spoilage\", \"temperature_range\": \"10-13°C\", \"storage_conditions\": \"Well-ventilated storage area with minimal light exposure, regular cleaning and sanitation\", \"post_harvest_handling\": \"Pre-cooling to 10-15°C, grading and sorting to remove damaged stalks, washing to remove dirt and debris\", \"expected_spoilage_time\": \"2-3 weeks under poor conditions (high temperature and humidity)\"}','{\"dosage\": \"Total 420 kg N, 180 kg P2O5, 180 kg K2O per hectare, split into 3 equal doses\", \"cautions\": \"Avoid over-fertilization, especially with nitrogen, as it can lead to water pollution and reduced sugar content\", \"npk_ratio\": \"180:90:90 kg/ha (at planting), 120:60:60 kg/ha (at 20 DAT), 90:45:45 kg/ha (at 40 DAT)\", \"micronutrients\": \"Zinc Sulphate 25 kg/ha, Boron 2 kg/ha, Manganese 10 kg/ha\", \"deficiency_signs\": \"Yellowing of leaves, stunted growth, reduced sugar content\", \"application_method\": \"Drip fertigation\", \"application_timing\": \"Basal dose at planting, top dressing at 20, 40, 60 days after transplanting (DAT)\", \"organic_alternatives\": \"FYM (Farm Yard Manure) 25 t/ha, Vermicompost 10 t/ha\", \"recommended_fertilizer\": \"DAP (18-46-0) + Urea (46-0-0)\"}','{\"harvest_method\": \"Mechanical combine or manual hand-picking\", \"harvest_duration\": \"12-14 months\", \"best_harvest_time\": \"Early morning, when dew is still present, to minimize juice loss and reduce the risk of contamination\", \"equipment_required\": [\"Sugarcane harvester\", \"Juicer or crusher\", \"Baler or bundler\"], \"harvest_indicators\": [\"Fruit color change from green to yellow\", \"Firmness test: 10-12 kg/cm²\", \"Leaf senescence: 50-60% of leaves turn yellow\", \"Brix level: 12-14%\"], \"post_harvest_losses\": \"Typical post-harvest loss: 5-10%, reduce by proper handling, storage, and transportation\", \"pre_harvest_interval\": \"At least 21 days after pesticide application\", \"yield_considerations\": \"Average yield: 60-80 tons/ha under good conditions, 40-60 tons/ha under poor conditions\", \"expected_harvest_date\": \"February-March\"}','{\"current\": {\"rain_mm\": 0.0, \"condition\": \"Mainly Clear\", \"feels_like_c\": 30.8, \"temperature_c\": 30.6, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.7, \"humidity_percent\": 47, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.0, \"wind_direction_deg\": 271, \"cloud_cover_percent\": 23}, \"latitude\": 18.506084, \"timezone\": \"Asia/Kolkata\", \"longitude\": 73.762169, \"fetched_at\": \"2026-06-18T11:51:10.034518Z\", \"forecast_7_days\": [{\"date\": \"2026-06-18\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 33.5, \"temp_min_c\": 23.2, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 19.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-19\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 34.2, \"temp_min_c\": 22.0, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 17.5, \"precipitation_mm\": 0.3}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-20\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 33.9, \"temp_min_c\": 23.0, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.0, \"precipitation_mm\": 3.5}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-21\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 32.5, \"temp_min_c\": 23.8, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 18.7, \"precipitation_mm\": 6.7}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-22\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm\", \"temp_max_c\": 30.7, \"temp_min_c\": 23.5, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 14.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 10.2}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-23\", \"condition\": \"Thunderstorm with Hail\", \"temp_max_c\": 25.5, \"temp_min_c\": 22.9, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 16.1, \"precipitation_mm\": 12.3}, {\"date\": \"2026-06-24\", \"condition\": \"Light Drizzle\", \"temp_max_c\": 27.1, \"temp_min_c\": 22.1, \"wind_speed_kmh\": 19.5, \"precipitation_mm\": 1.8}], \"agricultural_advisory\": [\"✅ Weather conditions are favourable for crop growth.\"]}','{\"ai_advisory\": {\"harvest_advice\": \"Plan for harvest in February-March, when the crop reaches maturity, as indicated by fruit color change, firmness, leaf senescence, and Brix level.\", \"storage_advice\": \"Store sugarcane in hermetic bags or silos with controlled ventilation, maintaining a temperature range of 10-13°C and humidity range of 85-90% RH, to preserve quality and extend shelf life.\", \"fertilizer_advice\": \"Apply the recommended fertilizer doses, including DAP (18-46-0) and Urea (46-0-0), following the specified NPK ratio and micronutrient guidelines.\", \"immediate_actions\": [\"Immediate Action 1: Continue with regular crop monitoring to detect any potential disease or pest issues early.\", \"Immediate Action 2: Ensure proper irrigation management to maintain optimal soil moisture levels, considering the current weather conditions.\"], \"irrigation_advice\": \"Water sugarcane crops when the top 10-15 cm of soil feels dry to the touch, avoiding overwatering, which can lead to disease susceptibility.\", \"farmer_action_plan\": {\"day_1\": [\"Inspect the field for any signs of disease or pests\", \"Check irrigation systems for proper functioning\"], \"day_2_7\": [\"Apply fertilizer as per the recommended schedule\", \"Monitor crop growth and development\"], \"week_2_4\": [\"Continue with regular crop monitoring and maintenance\", \"Plan for harvest preparations\"], \"long_term\": [\"Review and adjust the crop management plan as needed\", \"Explore opportunities for crop rotation and soil conservation\"]}, \"weather_precautions\": [\"Weather Precaution 1: Be prepared for potential heat stress and take measures to mitigate its impact on the crop.\", \"Weather Precaution 2: Monitor weather forecasts for any changes in temperature, humidity, or precipitation that may affect crop health or harvest timing.\"], \"disease_management_plan\": [\"Step 1: Maintain a clean and well-sanitized field environment to prevent the introduction of diseases.\", \"Step 2: Implement integrated pest management (IPM) principles, including cultural, biological, and chemical controls, as needed.\"]}, \"market_insights\": {\"price_trend\": \"Stable\", \"demand_trend\": \"Moderate\", \"nearby_markets\": [\"Local Market\", \"Regional Market\"], \"best_selling_time\": \"February-March, during the peak harvest season\", \"current_market_price\": \"₹25-30/kg\", \"expected_price_movement\": \"Prices are expected to remain stable in the next 30 days, with a potential for a slight increase during the peak harvest season.\"}, \"overall_summary\": {\"top_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress and drought stress due to high temperatures and low rainfall\", \"Risk 2: Potential for disease or pest outbreaks if proper management practices are not followed\"], \"crop_status\": \"Healthy\", \"health_score\": \"97.0/100\", \"urgency_level\": \"Low\", \"disease_status\": \"Healthy\", \"final_conclusion\": \"The sugarcane crop is currently healthy, with a high health score and no visible symptoms of disease. However, it is essential to continue monitoring the crop and implementing proper management practices to mitigate potential risks and ensure a successful harvest. The current weather conditions pose some risks, but with proper irrigation management and heat stress mitigation techniques, the crop can thrive. The market outlook is stable, with moderate demand and prices expected to remain stable in the short term.\", \"key_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Continue with regular crop monitoring and maintenance\", \"Recommendation 2: Implement integrated pest management (IPM) principles to prevent disease and pest issues\"]}, \"weather_analysis\": {\"humidity\": \"47%\", \"wind_speed\": \"18.7 km/h\", \"weather_risks\": [\"Risk 1: Heat stress due to high temperatures\", \"Risk 2: Potential for drought stress if rainfall remains low\"], \"harvest_advisory\": \"The current weather forecast does not indicate any immediate need to harvest the crop early, but continue to monitor the weather and crop conditions.\", \"rainfall_forecast\": \"Precipitation: 0.0 mm, Mainly Clear\", \"spraying_advisory\": \"It is not recommended to spray pesticides or fungicides today due to the high wind speed and potential for drift.\", \"current_temperature\": \"30.6°C\", \"weather_recommendations\": [\"Recommendation 1: Implement irrigation management strategies to mitigate drought stress\", \"Recommendation 2: Consider using shade or other heat stress mitigation techniques to protect the crop\"]}}','[{\"content\": \"Integrated Pest Management (IPM) principles: 1. Cultural control: Crop rotation, resistant varieties, sanitation. 2. Biological control: Predatory insects, Bt, Trichoderma. 3. Chemical control: Last resort, use registered pesticides at correct dosage. 4. Monitoring: Regular scouting every 5–7 days.\", \"metadata\": {\"type\": \"ipm\", \"source\": \"fao.org\"}, \"relevance\": 1.3}, {\"content\": \"Maize (Zea mays) grey leaf spot disease. Symptoms: rectangular grey-brown lesions parallel to leaf veins. Management: Crop rotation, resistant hybrids, triazole fungicides. Maize NPK: 150:75:75 kg/ha. Harvest at 25–30% grain moisture.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Maize\", \"source\": \"cgiar.org\", \"disease\": \"Grey Leaf Spot\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4436}, {\"content\": \"Cotton (Gossypium hirsutum) bollworm management: Inspect weekly during boll formation. Use pheromone traps for monitoring. Apply Bt-based biopesticides at early instar stage. Recommended NPK: 120:60:60 kg/ha with micronutrients.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Cotton\", \"source\": \"icar.org.in\", \"disease\": \"Bollworm\"}, \"relevance\": 1.4949}, {\"content\": \"Banana Sigatoka disease (Mycosphaerella fijiensis) management: Remove and destroy infected leaves. Apply systemic fungicides (propiconazole). Maintain plant spacing for air circulation. Banana requires 13–15 months from planting to harvest. Storage: 13–14°C, 90–95% RH. Shelf life: 1–4 weeks.\", \"metadata\": {\"crop\": \"Banana\", \"source\": \"fao.org\", \"disease\": \"Sigatoka\"}, \"relevance\": 1.5235}]',18.506084,73.762169,16.43,'completed','','2026-06-18 11:50:57.371787','2026-06-18 11:51:13.813205'),(100,'crop_images/b377c6a852e8446f8d746a3d5af9b762.png','','',0,'[]','',0,'','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','{}','[]',18.497297,73.782276,NULL,'processing','','2026-06-19 12:19:14.380635','2026-06-19 12:19:14.380635');
